review_text: Hati-hati buat yang pake maps krna kalau pakai jalan maps biasanya diarahkan dr blkg yg mana ga bs dilalui kendaraan. Tukang angkringan disitu juga bilang byk yg suka kesasar kesitu kalo pake maps. Ancer2nya dr pasar ngasem aja nnti ketemu pertigaan yg ada pohon beringinnya terus belok kiri kalo dr pasar ngasem, stlh itu lurus dah nyampek. Sekarang sy ulas menu2nya, waktu itu sy dipesankan bbrpa menu makanan. Favoritku dan aku rekomendasikan juga adalah java beer tapi lupa ga kefoto, selebihnya menu makanannya biasa aja rasanya. Dessertnya enaak tapi lupa namanya. Utk suasana tenang dan ayem dgn nuansa bangunan jawa.  Tempat bersih toilet bersih. Tapiii sgt disayangkan kolam air mancurnya bau menyengat, warnanya juga hijau. Waktu ksna ada pertunjukan tari juga. Dan disana juga ada galeri seninya jd bs sekalian keliling galeri seni. Dari segi pelayanan sudah bagus tapi ada karyawan yg menurut sy kurang ramah.

review_translated_text: Be careful for those using maps because if you use maps roads are usually directed from the block which cannot be passed by vehicles. The angkringan worker there also said that many people like to get lost there if they use maps. Just go from the Ngasem market and youll find a T-junction with a banyan tree, then turn left if you come from the Ngasem market, then go straight and youll reach it. Now Im reviewing the menus, at that time I ordered several food menus. My favorite and the one I also recommend is Java beer but I forgot not to take a photo, the rest of the food menu is just ordinary. The dessert is delicious but forgot the name. For a calm and serene atmosphere with the feel of a Javanese building. Clean place, clean toilet. But its a shame that the fountain pool has a strong smell, and the color is also green. At that time there was a dance performance too. And there is also an art gallery there so you can also go around the art gallery. In terms of service, it is good, but there are employees who in my opinion are not friendly.

If you want to go to the Royal Palace, dont forget to check the day of the week... I entered from the north side, but the location on Google Maps was incorrect, so I requested a correction. If you enter from here, you will go through the gallery and then through the courtyard, so it is a little difficult to understand, but if you follow the map you will get there. There are also several signboards on the premises. price is very reasonable Add sweets to your order I visited by myself, but the staff was very helpful and the atmosphere was nice, so I was able to enjoy a relaxing meal.

review_text: Berkesempatan menikmati menu Sultans Dishes yang terletak di area Keraton Yogyakarta. Konsep dining dengan menu rata rata tradisional khas Yogyakarta. Secara umum taste yang ditawarkan tidak sekedar manis dan legit seperti stereotip masakan Jawa namun juga gurih. Sebenarnya tidak ada menu khas atau yang paling direkomendasikan, karena tiap menu punya keunikan dan kelebihannya sendiri. Pelayanan ramah dengan hospitality seperti di hotel berbintang. Ruangan resto cukup luas dan ada beberapa spot duduk, kesan dan ornamen Yogyakarta yang kental.

review_translated_text: Have the opportunity to enjoy the Sultans Dishes menu which is located in the Yogyakarta Palace area. Dining concept with a traditional menu typical of Yogyakarta. In general, the taste offered is not just sweet and delicious like the stereotype of Javanese cuisine but also savory. Actually, there is no typical or most recommended menu, because each menu has its own uniqueness and advantages. Friendly service with hospitality like in a star hotel. The restaurant room is quite spacious and there are several seating spots, with a strong Yogyakarta impression and ornaments.

review_text: Makanan cenderung manis ya, mungkin karena lidah orang jawa yang cenderung manis. Aneh saja Garang Asemnya kok jadi manis hehehehe. review_translated_text: Food tends to be sweet, maybe because the Javanese tongue tends to be sweet. Its strange how the Garang Asem is so sweet hehehehe. In terms of service, its really OK, it just needs to be improved on the quality of the food and the place.

Ancer2nya dr pasar ngasem aja nnti ketemu pertigaan yg ada pohon beringinnya terus belok kiri kalo dr pasar ngasem, stlh itu lurus dah nyampek. Sekarang sy ulas menu2nya, waktu itu sy dipesankan bbrpa menu makanan. Favoritku dan aku rekomendasikan juga adalah java beer tapi lupa ga kefoto, selebihnya menu makanannya biasa aja rasanya. Dessertnya enaak tapi lupa namanya. Utk suasana tenang dan ayem dgn nuansa bangunan jawa.  Tempat bersih toilet bersih. Tapiii sgt disayangkan kolam air mancurnya bau menyengat, warnanya juga hijau. Waktu ksna ada pertunjukan tari juga. Dan disana juga ada galeri seninya jd bs sekalian keliling galeri seni. Dari segi pelayanan sudah bagus tapi ada karyawan yg menurut sy kurang ramah.

review_translated_text: Be careful for those using maps because if you use maps roads are usually directed from the block which cannot be passed by vehicles. The angkringan worker there also said that many people like to get lost there if they use maps. Just go from the Ngasem market and youll find a T-junction with a banyan tree, then turn left if you come from the Ngasem market, then go straight and youll reach it. Now Im reviewing the menus, at that time I ordered several food menus. My favorite and the one I also recommend is Java beer but I forgot not to take a photo, the rest of the food menu is just ordinary. The dessert is delicious but forgot the name. For a calm and serene atmosphere with the feel of a Javanese building. Clean place, clean toilet. But its a shame that the fountain pool has a strong smell, and the color is also green. At that time there was a dance performance too. And there is also an art gallery there so you can also go around the art gallery. In terms of service, it is good, but there are employees who in my opinion are not friendly.

Kamis 25 April kami dinner jam 7, dan ada live music dengan suara kencang yg merusak suasana. Kami mencari tempat yang enak buat ngobrol2. Dahulu pernah ke sini pas tidak ada live musicnya dan suasananya enak untuk ngobrol. Kali ini kami harus berbicara dengan suara keras agar tidak kalah dengan suara sound system nya. Untuk tempat, makanan, parkiran dsb sebenarnya okay. Hanya saja suara sound system terlalu keras sehingga merusak atmosfernya yg sebenarnya kalau tidak ada musiknya nyaman dan romantis menjadi tidak nyaman. Ada satu lagi kekurangannya. Karena lokasinya terbuka dan bersebelahan dengan pasar, ada lalat besar berkeliaran mendekati dan hinggap di makanan. Hal ini sangat mengganggu. Teman saya sampai berujar, kalau ini terjadi di US, kita bisa menolak dan tidak perlu membayar untuk makanan yg tidak higienis :)
review_translated_text: Thursday 25 April we had dinner at 7, and there was live music with loud noise which ruined the atmosphere. We are looking for a nice place to chat. Ive been here before when there wasnt live music and the atmosphere was good for chatting. This time we had to speak loudly so as not to be overshadowed by the sound of the sound system. In terms of location, food, parking, etc. its actually okay. Its just that the sound system is too loud so it ruins the atmosphere which, if there is no music, the comfort and romance becomes uncomfortable. There is one more drawback. Because the location is open and next to the market, there are large flies roaming around and landing on the food. This is very disturbing. My friend even said, if this happened in the US, we could refuse and not have to pay for unhygienic food :)

Minumannya juga tidak hambar (hilang rasa manisnya) krn kebanyakan es batu, dgn varian es teh manis, es jeruk, jus jambu merah, air putih dingin, dan es singkong (atau kolak itu ya, entahlah) yang awalnya saya kira es degan hehehehe. review_translated_text: Came here for iftar with extended family. Take the all u can eat package. A buffet is provided for large meals (rice and side dishes) and a buffet for snacks (drinks, fried foods and cut fruit). When the evening call to prayer approaches, please be patient in queuing because lots of people order all you can eat too hehehe. As for the taste of the food, its not bad at the price offered. Still taste of the cooking spices. The drinks are also not bland (lose their sweet taste) because there are mostly ice cubes, with variations of sweet iced tea, orange ice, red guava juice, cold water, and cassava ice (or kolak, I dont know) which at first I thought was iced, hehehehe. The atmosphere is pleasant with an outdoor garden feel. There is a fountain in the middle of the park. And there is a kind of viewing tower for photo spots, it seems.

review_text: Eatery outdoor yang cantik. Secret garden ini cantik banget konsep resto outdoor gitu, inget banget dulu pas kuliah, sekitar 10 tahunan yg lalu tempat ini pertama kali buka, jd langganan  makan cantik, cuma sekarang sayangnya tempatnya kurang terawat, cat-catnya banyak yang kusam, kolamnya kotor. Untuk pilihan makanannya bervariasi bgt, ada menu asian (seperti mie goreng atau mie rebus, nasi goreng, kwetiaw penang, iga bakar, sup iga dan lain lain) dan menu western (seperti spaghetti atau fettucini carbonara, aglio o olio, steak), snack-snack, dan minumannya (mulai dari wedang uwuh, matcha latte, dan lain-lain). Kemarin aku pesen carbonara fettucini, enak banget sih, asinnya dapat banget (creamy nya karena asinnya dapet, jadi kerasa creamy nya). Recommended sih carbonara fettucini nya. Ponakanku makan iga bakar kecapnya abis banyak banget. Adekku pesan sup iga katanya enak dan cukup empuk (kata dia  empuknya cocok bgt buat dia yg abis selesai operasi gigi). Tempat ini buka jam 15.00, kami kesana kemarin sekitar jam 15.15 an, sayangnya karena baru banget buka jadi menu nasi belum ready, baru ready jam 16.00, akhirnya kami pesan menu non nasi, dan adik saya yang pengen menu nasi alhamdulillah bisa ada di jam 15.45 an. Vibesnya asyik buat foto-foto dan nyore bareng, apalagi kalau malam lampu-lampunya pada nyala jadi indah. Yg jelas rasa makannnya lumayan enak. Bisa diulang kalo pengen ngajakin keluarga atau teman kumpul di tempat estetik (walaupun sayangnya sekarang kondisinya kurang terawat dibandingkan dulu) dan makanan yg cukup enak, dengan harga yang cukup terjangkau.
review_translated_text: Beautiful outdoor eatery. This secret garden has a really beautiful outdoor restaurant concept, I really remember when I was in college, about 10 years ago this place first opened, so it was a beautiful place to eat, but now unfortunately the place is not well maintained, a lot of the paint is dull, the pool is dirty. The food choices are very varied, there are Asian menus (such as fried noodles or boiled noodles, fried rice, Penang kwetiaw, grilled ribs, rib soup and others) and western menus (such as spaghetti or fettuccine carbonara, aglio o olio, steak), snacks -snacks and drinks (starting from wedang uwuh, matcha latte, etc.). Yesterday I ordered fettucini carbonara, it was really delicious, it was really salty (its creamy because its salty, so it feels creamy). The fettucini carbonara is recommended. My nephew ate grilled ribs with soy sauce and he used up a lot of it. My brother ordered rib soup, he said it was delicious and quite tender (he said the tenderness was perfect for him who had just finished dental surgery). This place opens at 15.00, we went there yesterday around 15.15, unfortunately because it just opened so the rice menu wasnt ready yet, it was only ready at 16.00, in the end we ordered the non-rice menu, and my sister who wanted the rice menu thank God it was available at 15.45 an. The vibe is fun for taking photos and relaxing together, especially at night when the lights are on, its beautiful. Whats clear is that the food tastes pretty good. You can repeat it if you want to invite your family or friends to gather in an aesthetic place (although unfortunately now it is in a less well-maintained condition than before) and the food is quite delicious, at quite affordable prices.

review_text: The location was good. It was about a 20 minute walk to the main Marlioboro street. Many restaurants, Warungs and street food stands in the area. There are also many mosques in the area, so you could hear 4 different mosques calling for prayer very loudly at least 5 times a day at the same time. Nice rooms: clean and tidy. The drinking water bottles were replenished daily. Air conditioning worked well. The pool was small, but refreshing and clean. Daily cleaning of the room. No extra roll of toilet paper in the bathroom, which means you have a problem if it suddenly runs out. Strange, bad smell in the room and hallway. They had air fresheners hanging in the hallway that regularly sprayed a pleasant scent. Elevators were very small: they could barely fit 4 people, without luggage. With our backpacks the two of us could just fit in there. Breakfast is traditional Indonesian: various preparations of rice, chicken, fish, soup and noodles. There was also a small salad and fruit bar, but there were regular fruit flies on it because it was not covered. I didnt eat any of this. There was also always a pot of black coffee and a pot of black tea hot, with sugar and milk powder next to it. The breakfast room was small, because sometimes a seat was not immediately available due to crowds. The service varied depending on which staff member was working. Some employees were friendly and service minded, but some were not. On Tuesday evening, April 9, there was a girl working in the Hypnotise restaurant who I think was not properly trained. She gave us the menu, walked away and didnt look back at us. We had closed our menus and tried to make eye contact with her for several minutes in vain, even waving didnt get her attention. It wasnt until we called her that she looked up from the computer. When we wanted to order, she told us that almost everything was already sold out, including our choices (both food and drinks). Instead of informing us in advance about what is no longer available, she wastes our time and disappoints us! We were hungry so we ordered something that was still available. When we received our order, it also turned out that she had not washed the ginger in my tea, so there was still dirt stuck to it and that my Chicken Katsu was still partially raw! All the girl kept doing was half-heartedly saying sorry. It didnt seem sincere at all. I spent the entire evening and the next day worried that I would develop symptoms from eating the raw chicken! To compensate, her manager deducted the tea and chicken dish from the receipt. It would have been nice of the employee and the manager if they had at least asked me how I was doing the next day.
review_translated_text: De locatie was goed. Het was ongeveer 20 minuten lopen naar de hoofdstraat  Marlioboro street. Vele restaurantjes, Warungs en standjes met streetfood in de omgeving. Ook heel veel moskees in de omgeving, waardoor je minstens 5 keer per dag zeer luid wel 4 verschillende moskees tegelijk hoorde oproepen tot het gebed. Fijne kamers: schoon en netjes. Dagelijks werden de flesje drinkwater aangevuld. Airco deed het goed. Het zwembad was klein, maar lekker verfrissend en schoon. Dagelijkse schoonmaak van de kamer. Geen extra rol wc-papier in de badkamer, waardoor je een probleem hebt als het opeens op raakt. Vreemde, onfrisse geur in de kamer en op de gang. Ze hadden op de gang luchtverfrissers hangen die regelmatig een prettige geur spoten. Liften waren erg klein: er pasten net 4 personen in, zonder bagage. Met onze backpacks pasten we er met ons tweeen net in. Ontbijt is traditioneel Indonesisch: verschillende bereidingen van rijst, kip, vis, soep en mie. Daarnaast was er een kleine salade- en fruitbar, maar daar zaten geregeld fruitvliegjes op, omdat het niet afgedekt was. Hier heb ik dan ook niets van gegeten. Ook stond er altijd een pot zwarte koffie en een pot zwarte thee warm, met suiker en melkpoeder ernaast. De ontbijtruimte was trouwens klein, want soms was er door drukte niet direct een zitplek beschikbaar. De service varieerde afhankelijk van welk personeelslid aan het werk was. Sommige medewerkers waren vriendelijk en servicegericht, maar sommigen niet. Op dinsdagavond 9 april stond er in het Hypnotise restaurant een meisje te werken dat volgens mij niet goed getraind was. Ze gaf ons het menukaart, liep weg en keek niet meer naar ons om. We hadden onze menus dichtgeslagen en probeerden minuten lang tevergeefs oogcontact met haar te maken, zelfs zwaaien trok haar aandacht niet. Pas toen we haar riepen, keek ze op van de computer. Toen we wilden bestellen, vertelde ze ons dat bijna alles al uitverkocht was, ook onze keuzes (zowel eten als drinken). In plaats van ons van te voren te informeren over wat er niet meer beschikbaar is, verdoet ze ons tijd en stelt ze ons teleur! We hadden honger en hebben toch iets besteld wat er nog wel was. Toen we onze bestelling kregen, bleek ook nog eens dat ze de gember in mijn thee niet gewassen had, waardoor er nog aarde aan plakte en dat mijn Chicken Katsu nog gedeeltelijk rauw was! Het enige wat het meisje telkens deed, was halfslachtig sorry zeggen. Het kwam totaal niet gemeend over. Ik was de hele avond en de volgende dag bang dat ik ziekteverschijnselen zou krijgen vanwege het eten van de rauwe kip! Ter compensatie heeft haar manager de thee en het kipgerecht van de bon afgehaald. Het had de medewerkster en de manager gesierd als ze mij de volgende dag ten minste hadden gevraagd hoe het met mij ging.

review_text: Good place to stay

Tempat long stay lainnya di Jogja. Pesan room Superior, tapi ternyata kamarnya kecil dan ada tonjolan di dinding yg bikin jalan masuk ke kamar makin sempit (gambar 1 & 2). Akhirnya komplain ke resepsionisnya, minta pindah kamar.  Awalnya kami minta pindah ke Superior aja gpp, yg penting tdk ada tonjolan itu supaya saya & Ibu saya bisa nyaman. But surprisingly dr pihak hotel memberikan free upgrade ke tipe Deluxe <3 Jadi saran aku nih buat kalian yg tdk biasa dengan ruangan sempit dan ada budget lebih, langsung aja reserv tipe Deluxe ya. Nyaman bgt! Apalagi room yg saya dapat jendelanya hadap sunrise. Jadi setiap pagi bisa berjemur sambil rebahan di kamar. Hhehe... Kondisi kamar same as pict di google ya.. toiletnya juga sama (tanpa bidet & shower paten). Jadi utk yg ngerasa kurang bisa bebersih tanpa bidet, bisa nyiapin gayung portable sebelum stay di sini. Utk toiletries nya lengkap. Botol sabun & shampo size imut (klo habis nanti diberi lagi waktu cleaning room). Trus gelas utk kumurnya pakai gelas plastik warna hitam (sangat kids-friendly)! Kasurnya nyaman & enak bgt buat punggung (med-firm), selimut tebal, tidak ditemukan debu di sudut kamar. AC nya dingin, water heater berfungsi dan bisa diatur, wastafelnya jg ada air hangatnya. Saran saya kalo bisa diberi tanda di kran shower & wastafelnya, agar tamu yg tdk familiar dengan kran model begitu bisa tahu ke arah mana utk menggunakan air dingin maupun hangat. Hotel ini dekat terminal, trus ada halte TransJogja juga, banyak makanan di sepanjang jalan, dekat circle K, Indomart, Alfamart, toko oleh2. Saya tdk ambil breakfast di hotel krn lebih prefer kulineran di pasar2 tradisional. Dr hotel ini bisa cari sarapan ke Pasar Ngasem (+- 20 mnt jalan kaki), hitung2 jogging yaa.. Catatan utk hotel : 1. Resepsionis di depan, tolong lbh ramah lagi ke tamu. Saya sering sekali keluar - masuk hotel, tp jarang dapat salam & senyum dr resepsionis. 2. Beri tanda pada kran di toilet kamar, mana yg air hangat & dingin. 3. Tolong basemen diberi lift dong, pegel bgt bawa koper / tas dr basemen ke Lobby. 4. Kenapa tidak menyediakan free refill mineral di lorong kamar??
review_translated_text: Another long stay place in Jogja. Ordered a Superior room, but it turned out the room was small and there was a bulge on the wall which made the entrance to the room narrower (pictures 1 & 2). Finally complained to the receptionist, asking to move rooms. Initially we asked to move to Superior, its okay, the important thing is there are no bulges so that my mother and I can be comfortable. But surprisingly the hotel gave a free upgrade to the Deluxe type <3 So my advice is for those of you who are not used to small rooms and have more budget, just reserve the Deluxe type. Very comfortable! Moreover, the room I got had a window facing the sunrise. So every morning you can sunbathe while lying in your room. Haha... The condition of the room is the same as the pic on Google... the toilet is also the same (no bidet & patent shower). So for those who feel like they cant clean without a bidet, you can prepare a portable ladle before staying here. The toiletries are complete. Cute sized bottles of soap & shampoo (if you run out, youll be given more cleaning room time). Then use a black plastic cup to gargle your mouth (very kid-friendly)! The mattress is comfortable & really good for your back (med-firm), the blanket is thick, you cant find dust in the corner of the room. The AC is cold, the water heater is functional and can be adjusted, the sink also has warm water. My suggestion is that you can put markings on the shower and sink faucets, so that guests who are not familiar with this type of faucet can know which way to use cold or warm water. This hotel is near the terminal, then there is a TransJogja stop too, lots of food along the road, near circle K, Indomart, Alfamart, souvenir shops. I didnt take breakfast at the hotel because I prefer culinary delights at traditional markets. From this hotel you can find breakfast at Ngasem Market (+- 20 min walk), count on jogging... Notes for hotels: 1. Receptionist at the front, please be friendlier to guests. I often go in and out of hotels, but rarely get a greeting & smile from the receptionist. 2. Mark the faucets in the toilet, which ones have warm and cold water. 3. Please give the basement an elevator, its really hard to carry suitcases/bags from the basement to the lobby. 4. Why dont you provide free mineral refills in the hallway?

Our stay was really great; we stayed here for 2 nights. Initially, we booked a room with twin beds because they were significantly cheaper than a double bed room when booking online. However, we were pleasantly surprised when the receptionist upgraded our room to a double bed for free. The hotel is nice and quiet, if you don t mind the nearby mosque. In our room, we only woke up once during the night due to the mosque prayers. Rooms: This Room was a solid 3+. The air conditioner in our room was noisy, it wasn t probably cleaned for long time. Only 2 pillows which for most people would be ok but for us wasn t enough. Safety: We felt super safe here. Food & drinks: This hotel has restaurant so if you want so stay by hotel you can enjoy meal here. Also good breakfast. Recomendo booking with breakfast.

Akhirnya setelah menepi, setelah dicek kondisi badannya, tidak terjadi sesuatu hal yg mengancam nyawanya namun akhirnya sayalah yang dimintai ganti rugi berupa uang. review_text: Golden Geisha di Jogja Paradise Foodcourt ini memang lain dari pada yg lain.. Mo makan aja butuh perjuangan.. Dtg 1/2 jam sblmnya ya.. Buka jam 12.00 utk mkn siang dan buka jam 17.00 utk mkn mlm.. dtg nulis waiting list dulu.. Kalo awal di list.. Buka lsg bs masuk.. Kl dah penuh ya 45 mnt kmd baru bs masuk.. Tapi..kuah ramennya.. review_translated_text: Golden Geisha at Jogja Paradise Foodcourt is really different from the others... It takes a struggle to just eat.. Come 1/2 hour beforehand... Opens at 12.00 for lunch and opens at 17.00 for dinner... come write down the waiting list first.. If youre first on the list.. Open it and you can come in.. If its full then itll take 45 minutes then you can come in.. But.. the ramen soup.. Its delicious.. second to none.. Its really a real broth.. You dont have to regret it queue first... If you go to Yogya you have to stop by here... Tuesday they are closed...

review_text: Rekomendasi resto yang homey. Tempatnya minimalis tapi artistik. Sudut-sudut ruangan banyak banget spot yg Instagramable. Ada indoor sama semi outdoor areanya. Agak pricey tapi oke, nggk mengecewakan. Makanannya enak, specially the chicken burger. Aku prefer chicken burger daripada beef burgernya. Racikan sausnya enak, nampol banget. Minumannya juga oke. Service nya juga ramah, komunikatif, dan humoris. Toilet bersih. Cashless available. Ada kang parkir yg bantu rapikan kendaraan.
review_translated_text: Homey restaurant recommendation. The place is minimalist but artistic. There are lots of Instagrammable spots in the corners of the room. There are indoor and semi outdoor areas. A bit pricey but okay, didnt disappoint. The food is delicious, especially the chicken burger. I prefer the chicken burger over the beef burger. The sauce mixture is delicious, really delicious. The drinks are okay too. The service is also friendly, communicative and humorous. Clean toilets. Cashless available. There is a parking attendant who helps tidy up the vehicle.

review_translated_text: Since its inception in 2017, it was just selling cakes until now it is full of selling F&B, I have never been absent every time I have been to Jogja, apart from the food being delicious, the atmosphere is homie and not to mention the service is very friendly and really Jogja, his name is Mas Didit who is ready to serve with all his heart and sincerity Every time you go to this place, Mas Didit always provides a room of satisfaction with his own service in addition to delicious food and drinks. review_text: Review ditulis di hari yang sama saat kunjungan. Ini pengalaman pertama kali datang ke sini. Kesan pertama : tempatnya adem banget. Terbilang nyaman, dingin ACnya, dan ada area outdoor juga. 5/5 untuk kenyamanan tempatnya. Semua menu makanan kosong (spaghetti/nasi/kentang) hanya tersedia bleger beef (blegger chicken kosong) dan minuman. Paling berkesan sama kopi koplo bia. Penilaian untuk kopi 5/5 enak banget, creamynya berasa padahal esnya udah mencair, dan single shot espressonya pas buat yang pengen ngopi ngopi ringan. Kalo pengen double shot, bisa pilih kopi koplo abi ya. Penilaian untuk blegernya 4/5 Suka sama saos mayonya, seperti racikan khusus karena cenderung manis. Tingkat serat dagingnya dan roti bun nya oke. Penilaian untuk pelayanan 3.5/5 Maaf untuk penilaian kasir kurang memuaskan sebab kasir beralasan uang pengunjung besar semua (diminta bayar pakai uang pas aja atau qris). Semoga ke depannya bisa lebih diatur lagi uang kecil yang tersedia di kasir. Untuk waiternya sangat ramah senyum. Nilai plus. Sehat sehat berkah selalu mas waiter. Aamiin. Fasilitas lainnya 4/5 Tersedia musholla dengan area yang cukupan, area indoor dan outdoor, dan toilet. Area parkir terbilang cukup terbatas. Toilet perempuan kurang pas untuk dikunci. Semoga segera diperbaiki demi keamanan dan kenyamanan customer. Untuk yang penasaran sama restonya kak Zaskia A Mecca, monggo mampir pinarak.
review_translated_text: Review written on the same day of visit. This is my first experience coming here. First impression: the place is really cool. It is said to be comfortable, the AC is cold, and there is an outdoor area too. 5/5 for the comfort of the place. All food menus are empty (spaghetti/rice/potatoes) only bleger beef (empty blegger chicken) and drinks are available. Most impressive is Koplo Bia coffee. Rating for coffee 5/5 Its really delicious, it feels creamy even though the ice has melted, and the single shot of espresso is perfect for those who want a light drink of coffee. If you want a double shot, you can choose Koplo Abi coffee. The rating for the blender is 4/5 I like the mayo sauce, its like a special concoction because it tends to be sweet. The fiber level of the meat and bread is okay. Rating for service 3.5/5 Sorry for the cashiers assessment which was less than satisfactory because the cashier argued that all the visitors money was large (they were asked to pay using just the right money or qris). Hopefully in the future we can better regulate the small money available at the cashier. The waiter is very friendly with a smile. Plus value. Always healthy, blessed, sir, waiter. Amen. Other facilities 4/5 There is a prayer room with sufficient area, indoor and outdoor areas, and toilets. The parking area is quite limited. The womens toilet is not suitable for locking. Hopefully it will be repaired soon for customer safety and comfort. For those who are curious about Sis Zaskia A Meccas restaurant, please stop by Pinarak.

review_text: Ke Mamahke untuk beli cake reguler double chocolate nya karena direcommend teman. Untuk tempatnya nyaman banget dan staff nya ramah banget, sabar ngejelasinnya. Untuk kue nya sendiri uniknya di tengah2 ada lapisan pastry gitu, dan cokelatnya tidak terlalu manis. Sayangnya pas saya datang yang ukuran reguler hanya tersedia yang double chocolate, redvelvet dan tiramisu. Tiramisu pun tinggal 1 dan keburu dibeli teman saya. Nextnya mau coba untuk yang keju karena secara pribadi saya lebih suka keju dripada cokelat.
review_translated_text: Went to Mamahke to buy the regular double chocolate cake because it was recommended by a friend. The place is very comfortable and the staff is very friendly, patient in explaining things. The unique thing about the cake itself is that there is a layer of pastry in the middle, and the chocolate is not too sweet. Unfortunately, when I arrived, the regular size was only available in double chocolate, redvelvet and tiramisu. There was only 1 Tiramisu left and my friend bought it in a hurry. Next, I want to try the cheese one because personally I prefer cheese over chocolate.

Fortunate coffee jogja needs to improve the quality and the taste of food. We ordered vegetable soup, tempeh hotdog, and bibimbap. The vegetable soup was pretty much just a bunch of veggies boiled in water. They couldnt just come up with recipe for the soup base?? No seasonings whatsoever. They made the tempeh tasted bad (somehow. The tempeh on its own is already good.) and the hotdog bun was dry and stiff and bland. The bibimbap didnt use the kochijunga sauce. It is hard to go wrong with such a simple memu like bibimbap if we just use store-bought gochujang sauce and they didnt even make it right. I also grabbed the peanut butter bread, which was stiff, stale, and had very little peanute butter. The staff were nice and friendly and I dont blame them at all for the poor quality of food. Whoever the owner is, they need to train their cook better and improve the recipe.

review_text: Saya sering datang ke tempat ini, tapi gatau kenapa di 2 January 2024 jam 19:51 servicenya tidak menyenangkan. Karena sering datang jadi saya hafal wajah2 pegawainya, namun di tgl 2 itu benar2 wajah baru, 1 perempuan ambil order dan 1 laki-laki yang antar pesanan ke meja. Biasanya kalo mau pesan pegawai2 sebelumnya sangat ramah, namun kali ini saya di tidak ada sapa atau apapun seperti biasa. Lalu setelah order saya disajikan oleh 1 pegawai laki-laki dia kembali ke area pegawai dan disitu dia mulai bernyanyi sangat keras mengikuti musik yang sedang di putar, disini saya sangat pusing dan terganggu. Posisi saat itu saya buka MacBook untuk melanjutkan kerjaan. Tidak hanga karaoke dari pegawai laki-laki yang mengganggu si pegawai perempuan juga sangat berisik di area pembuatan minuman saya sampai heran tidak biasanya dapat situasi seperti ini. Akhirnya saya memutuskan langsung pulang dengan makanan dan kopi masih utuh. Selain situasi yg tidak biasanya tersebut, mohon maaf sebelumnya tapi ketika pegawai laki-laki antar orderan saya ke meja itu sangat sangat bau ketek dan yg cium bukan hanya saya teman saya juga. Gimana bisa untuk bisnis fnb pegawai sebau itu? Mohon untuk HRD nya untuk kembali evaluasi pegawainya. Terima kasih 7/2/24 saya ubah review saya ke 5 stars karena sudah ada perbaikan, Terima kasih
review_translated_text: I often come to this place, but I dont know why on 2 January 2024 at 19:51 the service was not pleasant. Because I come often, I know the faces of the employees, but on the 2nd there were really new faces, 1 woman took the order and 1 man delivered the order to the table. Usually, if you want to order, the previous employees are very friendly, but this time I was not greeted or anything as usual. Then after my order was served by a male employee he returned to the employee area and there he started singing very loudly along with the music that was playing, here I was very dizzy and disturbed. At that time I opened my MacBook to continue working. There was no karaoke from the male employee who disturbed the female employee, it was also very noisy in the drink making area so I was surprised that this kind of situation is not usually found. Finally I decided to go straight home with my food and coffee still intact. Apart from this unusual situation, I apologize in advance, but when the male employee delivered my order to the table, his armpits smelled really bad and it wasnt just me, my friend, who smelled it. How is it possible for an FNB business for employees to smell like that? Please ask HRD to re-evaluate the employees. Thank you 7/2/24 I changed my review to 5 stars because there have been improvements, Thank you

review_text: Tempatnya nyaman, suasananya juga pas dan cocok. Interiornya modern dengan gaya vintage gitu. Karena masih pagi waktu itu, jadi indoor space masih panas, tapi its okay lah ya. Outdoor spacenya juga luas, enaknya  mengarah tepat ke luar jalan dari arah balcony. Jadi, viewnya bagus. Hal yang paling the bestnya dari cafe ini, tentu kopinya, ya! Emang kata-kata kopi legendaris itu tidak mengecewakan. Entah mengapa rasa kopinya sangat beda. Pahit tapi tidak terlalu pahit, kekentalannya juga pas. Among one of the top coffee shop I think. Aku juga coba makanan menunya, tapi hanya memesan snack pangsit goreng. Sangat disayangkan menurutku karena makanannya sedikit oily atau berminyak. But, it was good though. Nanti bakal update kalau sudah coba makanan beratnya. Lalu, layanannya juga cukup lama, mungkin karena pagi dan kokinya masih belum datang atau gimana who knows ya. Tapi, masnya ramah dan langsung minta maaf maaf karena cukup telat, dan ini menurutku sangat perlu dipuji sih. Tempat ini cukup direkomendasikan bagi teman-teman yang tinggal di jogja, sekitar atau dekat Sleman City Hall. Bagus buat nongki dan diskusi. Kalau study mungkin harus dipertimbangkan, karena nggak ada stop kontak untuk charger, ya, bagi yang bawa laptop. Tapi, kalau mau baca atau nulis doang, di sini ok juga. Edit: ternyata ada charger. Ya, teman-teman yang mau bawa laptop bisa datang. Lalu, makanan snack pangsitnya tetap aja oily, but I dont know. Apakah itu khas dari mereka? But still good though.
review_translated_text: The place is comfortable, the atmosphere is also right and suitable. The interior is modern with a vintage style. Because it was still early at that time, the indoor space was still hot, but thats okay. The outdoor space is also spacious, its nice to go right out onto the street from the balcony. So, the view is good. The best thing about this cafe is of course the coffee! Indeed, the words legendary coffee do not disappoint. I dont know why the coffee tastes so different. Bitter but not too bitter, the consistency is just right. Among one of the top coffee shops I think. I also tried the food on the menu, but only ordered the fried wonton snack. Its a shame in my opinion because the food is a little oily or greasy. But, it was good though. Ill update later when Ive tried the heavy food. Then, the service also took quite a long time, maybe because it was morning and the chef still hadnt arrived or who knows? However, the boss was friendly and immediately apologized for being quite late, and I think this really needs to be praised. This place is quite recommended for friends who live in Jogja, around or near Sleman City Hall. Good for hanging out and discussing. If youre studying, maybe you should consider it, because there are no sockets for chargers, for those who bring laptops. But, if you just want to read or write, its OK here too. Edit: apparently there is a charger. Yes, friends who want to bring a laptop can come. Then, the dumpling snacks are still oily, but I dont know. Is that typical of them? But still good though.

Mannernya untuk pegawai barista, kasir, waitress tolong dibenerin lagi. Tadi saya pesan mocca ada pricelist didepan kasir itu berbeda harga dengan harga asli. Harga pricelist mocca 20.900 sedangkan harga asli setelah bertanya jadi 29.000 tolong ini harganya jauh banget. At least kalau misal ada perbahan harga di update juga untuk pricelistnya bikin misleading soalnya. Pas saya bayar harganya jadi 32000, kami kaget dong trus saya tanya kok jadi mahal dan beda harga dengan pricelist dan jawaban mereka malah karna belum termasuk pajak. Tolong pajak 10% dari total harga minuman 20.900 gak mbgkin 12000 an kann. Giliran kita tanya kok bisa mahal baru dikasih tau kalau harganya naik dan pricelist itu belum diperbaharui dan itu sudah 2 minggu. Teman saya kasih saran malah jawabnya kayak ngeles bukannya minta maaf. Duhh gak ngerti lagi deh gimana sih SOP perusahaannya bukannya harus ada 3S ya. Seenggaknya dikasih tau sebelum pesan harganya dikasih tau dulu. Btw ini terjadi tanggal 12 Desember 2022 jam 16.30 sore. Thank you!
review_translated_text: Please improve the manners for baristas, cashiers and waitresses. When I ordered mocha, the price list in front of the cashier was different from the original price. The price list price for mocha is 20,900, while the original price after asking is 29,000, please, this price is really far away. At least, if for example there is a price change and the price list is also updated, it can be misleading. When I paid, the price was 32,000, we were shocked then I asked why it was so expensive and the price was different from the price list and their answer was because it didnt include tax. Please tax 10% of the total drink price of 20,900, it cant be 12,000, right? It was our turn to ask why it was so expensive, then we were told that the price had increased and the price list had not been updated and it had been 2 weeks. My friend gave me advice but he answered like he was gloating instead of apologizing. Duh, I dont understand what a companys SOP is, doesnt it have to have 3S? At least let them know before ordering, let them know the price first. BTW this happened on December 12 2022 at 16.30 in the afternoon. Thank you!

Suitable for hanging out, working or meetups. Because the mall is a bit quiet on weekdays, its still okay for calls and meetings. Recommended

There are regular table chairs and there are also those on the floor (on the 2nd floor). The one on the floor has a Japanese-style seating mat so your buttocks arent safe . WiFi is fast. Lots of plugs In the semi-outdoor model of a lesehan pavilion. Suitable for families. The bathroom and prayer room are clean Ample parking

Fasilitasnya juga memadai,  di lantai atas lesehannya nyaman privasinya terjaga ada toilet juga. Di bawah ada lesehan ada meja-kursi juga. Aula ada di bagian belakang. Model gazebo/ gubug juga ada. Lengkap sekali. Ada mushola yang bersih dan tertata dgn rapi, parkir luas. Banyak spot foto. Menunya bervariasi, masakan nusantara ada, western juga ada. Porsinya waoww.. Kenyang bgt. Harga terjangkau. Lemon tea dan juice Strawberrynya enakkk bingits. Recommended dehhh pokoknya.
review_translated_text: The place is comfortable, very spacious, the admin response is very good, the service is also good, the waiters are friendly, the food served is sterile and really kept clean. The facilities are also adequate, on the top floor the lesehan is comfortable and privacy is maintained, there is a toilet too. Below the floor there are tables and chairs too. The hall is at the back. Gazebo/hut models are also available. Very complete. There is a prayer room that is clean and neatly arranged, spacious parking. Lots of photo spots. The menu is varied, there are Indonesian dishes, there are also western dishes. The portion is wow... So full. Affordable prices. The lemon tea and strawberry juice are delicious. Recommended anyway.

review_text: Bubur hongkong nya beda dari semua bubur yang ada di Indonesia, karena buburnya emang resep dari korea, rasanya enak manis, gurih ditambah rempah yang membuat lengkap,enak banget.. Nyoba pesen nasi gorengnya juga yang di padu dengan rasa versi Chinese, Barat dan Lokal, pertama masuk ke dalam mulut itu domiman rasa khas Chinese, kemudian di pertengahan keluar rasa khas barat, dan di terakhir barulah rasa dari nasi goreng lokalnya keluar, nasi goreng yang tidak pernah saya rasakan di manapun Lain kali kalo kesini lagi mau nyoba menu yang bikin penasaran dan tak kalah enak dg restoran Dengan suasa tempat yang saya rasa cukup unik dan tradisional Dan terakhir tak kalah hebat, Chef nya orang Makasar mantan Chef dari Warung LAOTA di bali...
review_translated_text: Hong Kong porridge is different from all porridge in Indonesia, because the porridge is actually a recipe from Korea, it tastes delicious, sweet, savory with added spices which makes it complete, really delicious... Try ordering the fried rice which is combined with Chinese, Western and local flavors, first it enters your mouth with a typical Chinese taste, then in the middle the typical western taste comes out, and at the end the taste of the local fried rice comes out, plain fried rice. Ive never felt that anywhere Next time I come here, I want to try a menu that makes you curious and is no less delicious than the restaurant With the atmosphere of a place that I feel is quite unique and traditional And lastly, no less great, the chef is a Makasarese former chef from Warung LAOTA in Bali...

review_text: Resto terbaik yang pernah saya datangi selama ini, mulai dari bangunan, suasana, sampai makanannya top semua. Cocok buat pecinta musik dan fotografi, karena di setiap sudutnya penuh estetik semua. Tips bagi yang belum pernah ke sini adalah reservasi dulu via WA sebelumnya, kalian bisa lihat di IG nya @suaradewandaru. Klo mau ke restonya juga sebaiknya pakai kendaraan pribadi karena lokasinya yang agak terpencil. Menurutku sih masih bisa dijangkau perginya pakai transport online, pulang nya yang belum tentu bisa. Catatan juga bahwa di restonya belum tersedia mushola, namun di sekitar terdapat masjid yang berada di pemukiman warga, hanya dengan jalan kaki kurang dari lima menit saja dari resto
review_translated_text: The best restaurant Ive ever been to so far, from the building, atmosphere, to the food, everything is top notch. Suitable for music and photography lovers, because every corner is full of aesthetics. A tip for those who have never been here is to make a reservation via WA beforehand, you can see it on IG @warnadewandaru. If you want to go to the restaurant, you should also use a private vehicle because the location is quite remote. In my opinion, its still reachable to go using online transport, but its not necessarily possible to go home. Also note that the restaurant does not yet have a prayer room, but there is a mosque nearby which is located in a residential area, only less than a five minute walk from the restaurant.

review_text: Rent a car or bike to get here. Public transportation and ride hailing apps are out of the question. The place is off the beaten tourist path, but the roads are smooth. Internet signals are weak on the way, so you should download the area map beforehand if youre traveling solo. To book a table inside the cafe you have to contact them on their Whatsapp/Instagram and pay a deposit of non-refundable 100k which will go to your foods and drinks. Youll spend 75k and more anyway, so i think the deposit system is fine. On busy days your time is limited to 3 hours. You can definitely come without reservation, but i dont recommend it especially during rain season since it may drizzle outside. The food and drink is good, i love their mie letheg and fried tofu. Coffee is good. In general the menus are decently priced though not Jogja price. The atmosphere is serene and chill. The folks are nice. Since the cafe is far off, i wished there were more things to look for like books, arts, and whatnot.

I was probably a bit underdressed (compared to the Jakartans posing for their OOTDs), so when I got in, instead of greeting me the staff looked confused, and asked  ada yang bisa dibantu? , as if I had any intentions other than dining. The guy with glasses at the cashier was far from friendly, even when I corrected him for undercharging me. The food was terrible, the nasi bakar cumi at 50K was merely plain white rice with 3-4 slices of tiny squids and squid ink mixed in. No garlic, shallot, nor Thai basil. The bir pletok costed me 40K and it was so diluted I could barely taste any spices. Even warungs with just a fraction of their price can do better. When I went to the bathroom for just a few minutes, they took my plates away, although my stuff were obviously still on the table. Overall it was not a pleasant experience, I didn t feel welcome. The ambience was indeed nice, though.
Buka cuma weekend dan mesti reservasi dulu. Suasananya adem.

Makanan khasnya jadah dengan cocolan coklat. Enak, tidak banyak minyak dan manis coklatnya pas. Recommended.

review_translated_text: Accidentally found this place while staying in Kaliurang. The service is friendly and the place is semi outdoor. Most of the food and drinks come from their own garden. So, prices are affordable and fresh. The original chocolate is perfect for chocolate fans: bitter, without milk, and thick. Even drinks without chocolate are refreshing. I ordered ginger, lemongrass and mint leaves. The typical food is jadah with chocolate dip. Delicious, not a lot of oil and the chocolate is just right. Recommended.

review_text: Sebenernya ini adalah JCo yg nyamaaaann banget! Soalnya tempatnya tuh luas, dan ada 5 variasi area duduk, both indoor and outdoor. Seperti JCo yg lain (kecuali Reverse), JCo ini juga nempel sama BreadTalk. Jadi bisa jajan roti BreadTalk kalo lagi gak pengen donat. Please be notified kalo JCo ini adalah JCo yg kayak JCo kebanyakan, yaitu bakalan bising kalo lagi ada acara musik atau apapun yg pake sound system di main hall. Aku sih udah terbiasa sama kejadian kayak gini, jd gapapa. Yang penting aku bisa beli Jcoccino harga 35rb udah dapet yang gede   *ceritanya masih nyesek beli Iced Cappucino/Jcoccino di JCo Reserve*
review_translated_text: Actually, this is a really comfortable JCo! The thing is, the place is spacious, and there are 5 variations of seating areas, both indoor and outdoor. Like other JCo (except Reverse), this JCo is also attached to BreadTalk. So you can snack on BreadTalk bread if you dont want donuts. Please be notified that this JCo is a JCo that is like most JCos, that is, it will be noisy if there is a music event or anything that uses a sound system in the main hall. Im used to things like this, so its okay. The important thing is that I can buy Jcoccino for 35 thousand and I got a big one   *the story is that I still regret buying Iced Cappuccino/Jcoccino at JCo Reserve*

review_text: A nice place to chill around malioboro

I ordered a latte with almond milk because Im lactose intolerant. When I tried the coffee, it tasted like regular milk. I informed the woman at the counter, and she claimed she had made it with almond milk herself. The texture was different, but the taste was definitely that of regular milk. She didnt apologize or investigate further, but rather defended herself by insisting it was almond milk. Even if I was mistaken, I expected a better response to my complaint. I ended up ordering an americano because I couldnt continue drinking the latte. The male waiter apologized, which led me to give an extra star, but I was still very disappointed with how the woman handled the situation. It should be part of their training to understand that milk substitutions are not just about taste, but also about accommodating people who are genuinely allergic to regular milk.
Delicious coffee and drinks, friendly and professional staff. It has balcony with nice Malioboro view.

Pesen yg dingin2, dan disaranin oleh baristanya coconut late dengan basis espreso. Dan ternyata emang seenak itu, namun masih terlalu manis di lidahku, sehingga request 1 shot espreso biar rasa kopinya nendang.

review_text: Fatty! Itulah after taste yang tertinggal setelah menyantap semua hidangan yang kupesan saat itu. Mungkin rasa berlemak itu bisa diminimalisir dengan sajian minuman khas dari kedai ini. Sayangnya, kemarin aku lebih memilih untuk minum air mineral saja. Berikut untuk ulasannya: Nasi Ayam Opor Goreng Kecombrang (Rp29.000) Hidangan ini punya aroma kecombrang yang menonjol. Aku suka! Sayangnya daging ayam gorengnya kurang  flavorful.  Kuah opornya pun tidak terlalu spesial & menurutku agak sedikit membingungkan keberadaannya. Rasanya gurih manis dengan tekstur yang cukup kental. Sambal matahnya kemarin juga cenderung manis. Aku agak kesulitan menghabiskan hidangan ini karena cukup berlemak & manis. Khao Soi Ayam (Rp30.000) Sentuhan daun ketumbar, perasan jeruk nipis, dan acar bawang merahnya cukup membantu meringankan cita rasa yang  berat  dari hidangan ini. Untuk kuah karinya sendiri punya tekstur yang cukup kental dengan cita rasa yang gurih. Aku mau apresiasi pemilihan mienya! Sebab, tipe mie yang mereka pakai membuat kuah & bumbunya bisa menempel di badan mienya. Jadi, ketika dimakan, ada ledakan rasa di dalam mulut! Seru! Ngohiong (Rp20.000) Menu ini disajikan dengan saus khas thailand yang lagi-lagi manis. Ngohionya punya eksterior yang garing dan bagian dalamnya cukup juicy. Secara keseluruhan, makanan di sini enak. Cita rasanya cenderung gurih & manis khas masakan Asia Tenggara. Sayangnya, makanan ini terlalu berat & berlemak. Mungkin, kedepannya Parot Siramami bisa menyediakan hidangan penutup yang menyegarkan
review_translated_text: Fatty! That was the after taste left after eating all the dishes I ordered at that time. Maybe the fatty taste can be minimized by serving special drinks from this shop. Unfortunately, yesterday I preferred to just drink mineral water. Heres the review: Kecombrang Fried Opor Chicken Rice (Rp. 29,000) This dish has a prominent aroma of combrang. I like! Unfortunately the fried chicken meat is less flavorful. The opor sauce is not that special & I think its existence is a bit confusing. It tastes sweet and savory with a quite thick texture. Yesterdays sambal matah also tended to be sweet. I had a bit of difficulty finishing this dish because it was quite fatty & sweet. Khao Soi Chicken (Rp. 30,000) A touch of coriander leaves, lime juice and pickled red onions are enough to help lighten the heavy taste of this dish. The curry sauce itself has a fairly thick texture with a savory taste. I want to appreciate the noodle selection! Because the type of noodles they use means the sauce & seasonings can stick to the body of the noodles. So, when you eat it, there is an explosion of flavors in your mouth! Exciting! Ngohiong (Rp. 20,000) This menu is served with a typical Thai sauce which is again sweet. The ngohio has a crispy exterior and quite juicy inside. Overall, the food here is delicious. The taste tends to be savory & sweet, typical of Southeast Asian cuisine. Unfortunately, this food is too heavy & fatty. Maybe, in the future Parot Siramami can provide a refreshing dessert

review_text: Entah dapat dari sosmed mana sampe akhirnya nyasar ke sini buat hunting kuliner di kota Istimewa ini. Tempatnya cukup kecil, tetapi sungguh artistik. Karena datangnya pas lagi libur panjang, ujung-ujungnya yang datang orang Jakarta lagi klo didengar dari cara ngomongnya. Kali ini nyicipin Khao Soi nya, ini juga jadi salah satu alasan datang ke sini karena belum nemu di Jakarta yang konsep restonya kayak gini. Rasanya sih cenderung gurih, suapan pertama masih enak, begitu suapan kedua dan seterusnya jadi agak enek gitu, syukurlah makanannya masih bisa tak habisin wkwkw. Isiannya ada mie yang agak lebar sedikit, teksturnya juga sebagian basah dan sebagian kering gitu, mungkin itu pangsit gorengnya kali ya, kurang tau juga wkwkwk. Ditambah ayam suwir dan sedikit sayuran jadi rasanya ada sensasi herbalnya. Paling mantep mocktailnya sih, saya pesen Coffee Sour, rasanya ada pahit dari kopinya, manis dan agak smokey sikit dari kayu manisnya. Cocok buat mengimbangi makanannya yang full rempah itu.
review_translated_text: I dont know where I got it from social media until I finally got lost here to hunt for culinary delights in this special city. The place is quite small, but really artistic. Because he came when he was on a long holiday, in the end the people who came were Jakartans again, if you heard the way they spoke. This time I tried Khao Soi, this is also one of the reasons for coming here because I havent seen one in Jakarta with a restaurant concept like this. The taste tends to be savory, the first bite is still delicious, the second bite and so on becomes a bit delicious, thank God I cant finish the food hahaha. The filling contains noodles that are a bit wide, the texture is also partly wet and partly dry, maybe its the fried dumplings, I dont know hahaha. Add shredded chicken and a little vegetables so it has a herbal sensation. The most delicious mocktail, I ordered the Coffee Sour, it tasted bitter from the coffee, sweet and a little smokey from the cinnamon. Suitable to balance the food which is full of spices.

Menjajal rumah makan khas asian yang beda, dengan menu menu menarik yang dikemas cocok dengan lidah lokal. Lokasinya di tengah kota, cocok banget abis jalan-jalan di Malioboro trus mampir ke sini. Di dalam gang kecil ternyata ada rumah makan mungil minimalis terselip. Kali ini saya coba gohyong dan khao soi ayam, keduanya cakep bgt sih, well executed  , khao soi ayamnya sih kaya unknown bgt di lidah tapi tetep sopan lewatnya  . Rasa karinya beda dari kari japanese atau korean, pun ga kecina-cinaan juga. Masakan dari Ciang Mai, Thailand yang udah disesuaikan dengan budaya dan lidah kita, jadi sopan bgt ni pak bertamu di mulut pertamanya. Berkesan bgt dah. Kondimen bawang merahnya itu cakep bgt kalo pas kena gigit!!! Jangan lupa aduk terus biar semua kerasa sampe dalem-dalemnya. Suasananya nyaman bgt, kaya slow bar dan intimate dinning yg ga formal. Cocok bgt kalo mau bawa temen-temen, biar bisa comot sharing banyak menu. Love sekebon buat mas Wulang dan Mba Chel
review_translated_text: Try out different typical Asian restaurants, with interesting menus packaged to suit local tastes. The location is in the middle of the city, really suitable after walking around Malioboro and then stopping here. In a small alley, it turns out there is a small, minimalist restaurant tucked away. This time I tried gohyong and khao soi ayam, both were really delicious, well executed  , the khao soi ayam was really unknown to the tongue but still polite to pass  . The taste of the curry is different from Japanese or Korean curry, and its not Chinese either. Cuisine from Ciang Mai, Thailand which has been adapted to our culture and tongue, so its very polite for you to visit us on your first visit. Its very effective. The red onion condiment is so delicious when you bite into it!!! Dont forget to stir continuously so that everything is thoroughly mixed. The atmosphere is really comfortable, like a slow bar and informal, intimate dining. Its really suitable if you want to bring friends, so you can share lots of menus. Love sekebon for Mas Wulang and Mba Chel

review_text: Parot Siramami adalah singkatan dari Pagi Roti Siang Rame Malam Mie. Keren kan? Tempat ini dimiliki oleh duo artsy yang ternyata memang gemar kulineran across Asia Tenggara dan pandai memasak. Selain tempatnya sangat indie dan artsy, juga homy jadi berasa humble. Tempat homy itu memang selalu menyenangkan, seperti makan di rumah saudara jauh yang pandai memasak. Menunya juga beragam, ada nasi lemak, pad kra pao, tom yam, juga jangan lupa cobain es krimnya.. itu sangat sangat lezat. Harganya juga affordable untuk UMR Jogja yang minim ini, cocoklah kalau cuma makan seminggu sekali ke sini, yaitu 20K - 50K udah dijamin kenyang. Kalau ngga mau makan berat, makan snack-snack atau mocktailnya cucok banget.
review_translated_text: Parot Siramami is an abbreviation of Morning Bread, Lunch Rame, Evening Noodles. Cool, right? This place is owned by an artsy duo who apparently love culinary delights across Southeast Asia and are good at cooking. Apart from being a very indie and artsy place, it is also homely so it feels humble. A homely place is always fun, like eating at the house of a distant relative who is good at cooking. The menu is also varied, there is nasi lemak, pad kra pao, tom yam, also dont forget to try the ice cream... its very, very delicious. The prices are also affordable for Jogjas minimal minimum wage, which is suitable if you only eat here once a week, namely 20K - 50K and you are guaranteed to be full. If you dont want to eat a heavy meal, snacks or mocktails are really good.

Even though the menu doesnt have jumbo and regular options, the portions should be the same, right? As for the not bad taste, even the first bite tastes good but after a while it becomes salty. I think if you use pickles it would be better so it doesnt taste salty but there arent any pickles. When I was almost done, I found out that I could actually ask for pickles. review_translated_text: Sorry to share an unpleasant experience when buying liters. I bought it at the Gamping outlet near Gamping sub-district. When I arrived there were no employees at the front, I had to wait a few moments before they appeared when called. The time is today Friday, August 5 2022 at 15.30. I bought a drink that cost 13k using 100k cash. His brother asked whether he had exact money or not, I answered that there was no exact money. His older brother said pleasantly please exchange the money at the shop next door automatically I said ME? And I didnt want to because I was the one buying the food and I was the one exchanging the money. Instantly, his brothers expression became different and he seemed forced to exchange money at the shop next door. I just regretted that his brothers attitude was not polite at all, he didnt serve him in a friendly manner, he didnt smile. And the attitude that TELLS buyers to exchange money in a fierce tone. It shouldnt be like that, as a waiter you have to serve customers wholeheartedly and you have to be friendly.

review_text: Lokasi mudah ditemukan karena berada di pinggir jalan. Parkiran luas, teduh dan gratis. Susana resto nya seperti warung makan biasa. Banyak permainan untuk anak. Banyak tanaman hias dijual termasuk budi daya jamur nya juga yang bisa mengedukasi. Menu makanannya pengen dicoba semua karena merupakan olahan berbagai macam jamur. Rekomendasi jamur pedas nya.. tak kalah nila bakarnya nya juga manis dan gurih ke dalam dalamnya. Jus nya juga kental sekali. Untuk harganya agak mahal tapi sebanding dengan porsinya yang banyak dan lezat. Pesan 1 lauk bisa untuk 2 orang. Jadi enaknya kalo ke sini rame rame. Terdapat kolam ikan hias dan ikan terapi yang bisa dipakai. Terdapat ruang laktasi dan Kamar mandi juga banyak. Staff nya ramah dan ngebantu banget. Ada toko oleh oleh nya juga..cocok buat transit wisata. Vegetarian options: Banyak menu olahan jamur Dietary restrictions: Tidak banyak mengandung kolesterol Parking: Parkiran sangat luas dan teduh Kid-friendliness: Banyak wahana permainan anak
review_translated_text: The location is easy to find because it is on the side of the road. Parking is spacious, shady and free. Susana restaurant is like an ordinary food stall. Lots of games for children. Many ornamental plants are sold, including mushroom cultivation, which can also be educational. Everyone wants to try the food menu because it is made from various kinds of mushrooms. Recommended spicy mushrooms... no less delicious, the grilled tilapia is also sweet and savory inside. The juice is also very thick. The price is a bit expensive but worth it for the large and delicious portions. Order 1 side dish for 2 people. So its nice when its crowded here. There are ornamental fish ponds and therapeutic fish that can be used. There are also many lactation rooms and bathrooms. The staff is friendly and very helpful. There is a souvenir shop too... suitable for tourist transit. Vegetarian options: There are lots of processed mushrooms on the menu Dietary restrictions: Doesnt contain much cholesterol Parking: Parking is very spacious and shady Kid-friendliness: Lots of childrens play rides

review_text: Restoran yg sangat rekomended untuk dicoba, karena makanannya unik, ada sate jamur, pepes jamur, tongseng jamur, dan makanan lainnya yg serba jamur, tapi kalo gak suka jamur disini ada alternatifnya seperti ayam goreng dan ikan goreng. Rasa makanannya memuaskan, walaupun serba jamur tapi bisa membuat orang yg tdk suka jamur jadi ketagihan. Pelayanan disini sangat baik, pelayan cepat dan ramah, sehingga kita tdk perlu nunggu lama utk makanan datang. Suasana makan disini membuat nyaman, area sekitar hijau2 dipenuhi tanaman, dan tempatnya luas. Tapi kalo makan disini harganya lumayan bikin kaget untuk orang jogja, ditambah lagi dimenu tdk ada keterangan harga makanan, tapi okelah buat coba2, masih rekomended
review_translated_text: A highly recommended restaurant to try, because the food is unique, there are mushroom satay, mushroom pepes, mushroom tongseng, and other dishes that are all about mushrooms, but if you dont like mushrooms here there are alternatives such as fried chicken and fried fish. The taste of the food is satisfying, even though it is all mushrooms, it can make people who dont like mushrooms addicted. The service here is very good, the waiters are fast and friendly, so we dont have to wait long for the food to come. The atmosphere of eating here is comfortable, the surrounding green area is filled with plants, and the place is spacious. But if you eat here the prices are quite surprising for Jogja people, plus there is no information on the food prices on the menu, but its okay to try, still recommended

review_text: Salah satu rekomendasi tempat makan yang wajib banget kamu cobain. Lokasinya berada di jl. Kabupaten Menu yang paling laris dan rekomendasi adalah teh tariknya. Rasa teh tariknya mantapppp banget. Aku kemarin cobain teh tarik hijaunya dan aku puas banget sama rasanya. Gokilll Untuk menu makananya sendiri menurut aku rasanya biasa aja. Gak terlalu istimewa. Jadi memang orang banyak datang kesini karena pengen nyobain teh tarik dan varian minuman lainnya. Cuma sayangnya disini kalau lagi weekend antrinya panjang, jadi mungkin harus sangat sabar menunggu pesanan datang. Tapi pelayanannya cukup baik, dan suasana tempat makannya enak dan syahdu banget Untuk setiap weekend, ada live musicnya juga Parking: Banyak tempat parkir untuk motor, dan ada penjaga parkir yang mengatur keluar masuknya kendaraan. Namun untuk parkir mobil sedikit lebih sempit. Namun masih bisa di koordinasikan dengan penjaga parkir
review_translated_text: One of the recommended places to eat that you really have to try. The location is on Jl. Regency The most popular and recommended menu is the Teh Tarik. The taste of the pulled tea is really good. Yesterday I tried the green tea and I was really satisfied with the taste. Gokilll As for the food menu itself, I think it tastes just ordinary. Not too special. So a lot of people come here because they want to try Teh Tarik and other drink variants. Its just a shame that here on weekends the queues are long, so you may have to be very patient waiting for your order to arrive. But the service is quite good, and the atmosphere of the place to eat is really nice and serene For every weekend, there is live music too Parking: There are lots of parking spaces for motorbikes, and there are parking guards who regulate the entry and exit of vehicles. However, the car park is a little narrower. However, it can still be coordinated with the parking guard

review_text: Cafe near my house, always busy but now the menu is varied, the food is delicious, the view is beautiful, you can get the vibes. Unfortunately there is no car parking space, but there is someone who helps with parking. I like the fried noodles/godog, the Teh Tarik is great, the ice tape and lemongrass ice are also delicious. review_text: Kesini karena ingin nyoba teh vanilla dan teh tariknya karena kami memang suka. Datang untuk buka puasa tanpa reservasi alhamdulillah masih dapat tempat di tepi kolam. Camilan cuma pesan pisang coklat dan mendoan, rasanya enak tanpa gagal walau tidak istimewa, kami terbiasa banyak meisis/keju/topping nya sedangkan disini ya seperti umumnya gitu, ga melimpah. Oya disini juga diberi buka puasa sebagai pelengkap gratis. Ada musholla cukup untuk 3 orang dan bersih. Mengenai tempat, dengan tema kebun dan kolam air mancur, disini termasuk terpelihara sekali kebersihan nya, tidak ditemukan banyak nyamuk atau serangga yang mengganggu jadi bisa santai menikmati makanannya. Terima kasih sebelum nya, semoga terjaga kualitasnya dan kebersihan tempatnya.
review_translated_text: Came here because I wanted to try the vanilla tea and the pulled tea because we really like it. Came to break the fast without a reservation, thank God we still got a place by the pool. For snacks, just order chocolate banana and mendoan, it tastes delicious without fail even though its not special, were used to having lots of meisis/cheese/toppings whereas here its like that in general, not abundant. Oh yes, there is also free breaking of the fast here as a complement. There is a prayer room enough for 3 people and it is clean. Regarding the place, with a garden and fountain theme, the cleanliness is maintained here, there are not many mosquitoes or annoying insects so you can relax and enjoy your food. Thank you in advance, I hope the quality and cleanliness of the place is maintained.

review_text: Untuk harga secara overall kok agak overpriced ya. Kami bertiga makan+minum masing-masing satu porsi plus pisang goreng satu habis 140 ribu, belum parkir. Artinya satu orang habis hampir 50 ribu. Wow!! Tempatnya bagus dan luas. Enak juga buat nongkrong. Teh tariknya juara apalagi yang hijau. Kalau makanan, kami nyobain makanan ringan yaitu pisang goreng, enak banget. Sayangnya untuk makanan utamanya agak biasa saja. Nasi goreng tampilannya enak, teksturnya saya suka, jenis yang kering, tapi bumbunya agak kurang dikit. Mie gorengnya oke sih. Mie godognya kurang kalau menurut saya. Bukan yang buruk banget, tapi juga gak spesial, apalagi untuk harga segitu yang di tempat lain bisa dapat telur bebek dan dagingnya ayam kampung. Yang ini tidak kelihatan kalau pakai 2 bahan tersebut. Parking: Kami mengira tidak ada tukang parkirnya karena saat kami datang tidak ada yang membantu mengarahkan atau menyiapkan tempat. Hanya ada mas-mas ngobrol di warung kelontong sebelahnya. Saat mau pulang juga motor saya tidak dipersiapkan. Istri yang pake motor sendiri juga tidak dibantu padahal kesusahan saat berusaha melipat standar tengah.
review_translated_text: As for the overall price, its a bit overpriced. The three of us ate + drank one portion each plus one fried banana for 140 thousand, without parking. This means that one person spends almost 50 thousand. Wow!! The place is nice and spacious. Its also good for hanging out. The Teh Tarik is a winner, especially the green one. As for food, we tried the snack, namely fried banana, it was really delicious. Unfortunately the main food is rather ordinary. The fried rice looks delicious, I like the texture, the dry type, but the seasoning is a bit lacking. The fried noodles are okay. The godog noodles are lacking in my opinion. Its not really bad, but its not special either, especially for that price where you can get duck eggs and free-range chicken meat in other places. This one is not visible if you use these 2 ingredients. Parking: We thought there was no parking attendant because when we arrived there was no one to help direct us or prepare the place. There were just guys chatting at the grocery stall next door. When I wanted to go home my motorbike was not prepared. The wife, who was using her own motorbike, was also not helped even though she was having difficulty trying to fold the middle stand.

Suka sama tempatnya aja yg bs liat sawah Cm Sedih banget kmrn pas kesini sore niatnya mampir skalian liat sunset , kmrn beli grill, shabu, jus strawberry, es doger, sm niatnya beli teh poci (harganya 20k. ) Tapi, Sengaja all varian teh di offkan,pdhl ada sekitar 10an menu varian Teh,  masa iya jualan teh doank dioffkan Kak, Perlu diketahui hasil survey di Indonesia itu es teh adalah minuman dengan jumlah laku tertinggi dibanding minuman lain,alias COR menu no.1 ,ga ada ruginya sama sekali kl mau diadainpun, , beli kek bahannya diwarung sebelah ,saya tau maksdnya spy ningkatin sales,cm caranya aja yg keliru, butuh aktiv buat upselling sendiri dr pihak kasir atau waiter kl mau naikin penjualan, jgn main close menu gt aja. Lagian varian teh juga dijual mahal pasti untunglah. Es teh 1 gelas 16k juga hrganya kl ga slh. Cek juga itu penyimpanan cuminya kak, asli amis e poll :( Trus akhirnya beli mineral berharap yg dtng pake botol , ternyata pake gelas di press di bill dgn ukuran 500ml ,hrg 7k ,duhh mayaan soyo bathi wkwk. Udh gitu pas makan grill ga dikasih saos pedesnya, harusnya itu udh otomatis disediakan, orang itu pelengkap standart kok, saya udh 2x kesini, dl sm temen jg gt, minimal ditanyain dong itu mau tambah cabe potong enggk, atau mau pake saos egk ,ealah Skrng persaingan bissnis udh bnyk, mbokya bersyukur dan dirawat customer yg udh luangin waktu kesitu tuh, mumpung masih rame juga. Gt aj sii, just masukan aj, mau diperbaiki monggo ,egk jg silahkan kl mau lbh bnyk cust yg kecewa lagi. Thanks ya:)
review_translated_text: The expensive price is not commensurate with the quality and service. I just like the place where you can see the rice fields Cm Im really sad when I came here in the afternoon with the intention of stopping by and seeing the sunset, then I bought a grill, shabu, strawberry juice, doger ice, and my intention was to buy a pot of tea (the price was 20k.) But, deliberately all tea variants were turned off, even though there are around 10 tea variants on the menu, why dont selling tea just turn it off, Sis? Its important to note that the survey results in Indonesia show that iced tea is the drink with the highest sales compared to other drinks, aka COR menu no. Its just the wrong method, you need to be active in upselling yourself from the cashier or waiter. If you want to increase sales, dont just play close menu. Besides, the tea variants are also sold at a high price, so thats a good thing. 1 glass of iced tea is also 16k if you dont choose the price. Also check the squid storage, sis, its really fishy e poll :( Then finally bought the mineral hoping it would come in a bottle, but it turned out to be a glass, pressed on the bill with a size of 500ml, the price was 7k, duhh Mayaan soyo bathi hahaha. Thats the case when you eat the grill, you dont get spicy sauce, it should be automatically provided, that person is a standard complement, Ive been here twice, with friends too, at least ask if you want to add chopped chilies or not, or do you want to use other sauce, thats it. Now that there is a lot of business competition, Mbokya is grateful and cared for by customers who have taken the time to go there, while its still busy. Thats fine, just put it in, if you want to fix it, please, dont worry if you want more customers to be disappointed again. Thanks yeah :)

review_translated_text: I could say that this place was a hidden gem. The location is in a housing complex, its a bit complicated, but GPSaps is very, very helpful. The place is surprisingly spacious even though its only in the yard of the house. Cozy too.. Your fewd n baverages tho! Such a LEGIT! When it arrived it looked a little small but it turned out to be very full. I ordered the butter chicken *its delicious, but its a bit sweet for me who doesnt like sweets. salted egg chic *this is really true, the fried egg is really beautiful. know petis. mix platter *which contains fries, onion rings, chicwings, a bit different from other coffeeshops. The berry french toast *honey sauce wasnt good at all. Berry mocktail *this is really fresh. with green tea. NOTHING FAILS! Everything is mouth-watering! Unfortunately its far from the city center hwhwhwhw. Def go back to try the honey chic. Overall, so cool and would satisfy your stomach. Not only is the appearance beautiful, but the taste is also considered. Worth the price!

review_text: Lots of food variants with normal price, and also flavored milk beverages option.

Buat yang punya anak kecil, jangan lupa dikasih lotion / minyak kayu putih anti nyamuk dulu karena tempatnya banyak pohon dan outdoor jadi banyak nyamuk. Beberapa spot kursinya kurang bersih, tapi masih ok kalau dapat tempat yang bersih. Tempatnya ramai dan cenderung lebih banyak anak muda. Harga sangat terjangkau dan makanannya juga enak. Overall memuaskan. Will definitely come back. Vegetarian options: Bukan buat vege sih Dietary restrictions: Bukan opsi buat diet Parking: Ada di depan samping restonya, lumayan luas cukup buat 10-20 motor tapi dempet2an. Kalau mobil cuma bisa di pinggir jalan aja parkirnya. Kalau malam agak gelap tapi karena hanya ada 1 lampu jalanan. Kid-friendliness: Kalau anaknya suka outdoor ok, cuma pastikan sudah pakai anti nyamuk dulu. Tidak ada mainannya. Wheelchair accessibility: Agak susah sih kalau pakai ini, tidak memungkinkan karena banyak jalan setapak dan tangga.
review_translated_text: For those of you who have small children, dont forget to give them anti-mosquito lotion/eucalyptus oil first because the place has lots of trees and the outdoor area has lots of mosquitoes. Some of the seat spots are not clean, but its still okay if you get a clean place. The place is busy and tends to have more young people. Prices are very affordable and the food is also delicious. Overall satisfactory. Will definitely come back. Vegetarian options: Not for vegan though Dietary restrictions: Not an option for dieting Parking: Its in the front next to the restaurant, quite spacious enough for 10-20 motorbikes but close together. If you have a car, you can only park it on the side of the road. At night its a bit dark because there is only 1 street light. Kid-friendliness: If your child likes the outdoors, thats OK, just make sure they use mosquito repellent first. There are no toys. Wheelchair accessibility: Its a bit difficult to use this, its not possible because there are lots of paths and stairs.
