Menurut aku, tempat ini kurang oke kalau untuk nongkrong lama. Karena tempatnya relatif kecil dan kebanyakan orang yang kesini ya untuk kerja sepertinya (karena membawa laptop). Tapi seru sih. Definisi menikmati Jogja, kerja dari cafe, sambil slow living Notes: - Bisa payment dengan QRIS - Tidak ada retribusi parkir - Ada Resort di bagian belakang cafe ini Enjoy! Semoga terbantu!
review_translated_text: Suddenly visit here. Early meeting. Finally to Sapulu! It turns out its been open here since 7 am. The menu is more western. But everything is delicious! In my opinion, this place is not good for hanging out for a long time. Because the place is relatively small and most people come here for work, apparently (because they bring laptops). But its fun. The definition of enjoying Jogja, working from a cafe, while slow living Notes: - Can pay with QRIS - There are no parking fees - There is a Resort at the back of this cafe Enjoy! Hope this helps!

review_text: Random ke sini sama anak dan suami, ternyata tempatnya lucu, pengunjungnya kebanyakan bule. Di sini juga ada airbnbnya. Staffnya sangat ramah, hospitalitynya juara, mungkin karena standarnya tinggi ya, beda dengan kafe2 lain yg kebanyakan dikunjungi warga lokal. Staff sangat atentif terhadap kebutuhan kami, apalagi kami membawa anak balita. Mulai dari ditawarkan meja yg lebih luas, diambilkan peralatan makan karena lihat kami sharing makanan. Porsi makanannya cukup banyak, jd anak saya tidak bisa menghabiskan makanan sendirian. Ownernya juga sangat humble dan ramah menyapa kami. Anak saya diberi mainan. Selain itu, saya juga melihat ownernya memberikan minuman hangat secara cuma2 untuk lansia yg berjualan kayu.
review_translated_text: Randomly came here with my children and husband, it turns out the place is cute, the visitors are mostly foreigners. There is also an Airbnb here. The staff are very friendly, the hospitality is top notch, maybe because the standards are high, different from other cafes which are mostly visited by local residents. The staff was very attentive to our needs, especially when we brought a toddler. Starting from being offered a wider table, eating utensils being taken because they saw us sharing food. The food portions are quite large, so my child cant finish the food alone. The owner is also very humble and friendly in greeting us. My child was given a toy. Apart from that, I also saw the owner giving free hot drinks to elderly people who sell wood.

review_text: Even though the place is not very large, it is quite comfortable The food and drink are delicious

We came across this coffee place by coincidence and really liked it. The staff were really friendly and tried very hard to explain in English when we had questions. The atmosphere was very nice with the sound of running water and all the plants. Perfect place to hide from the heat and take a break. I tried their Kopi Susu Regal and really enjoyed it. It s basically coffee with milk and crumpled Regal biscuits on top. I might try to make it at home.
Tempatnya sangat nyaman, asri, ownernya juga sangat ramah. Menu2nya enak banget.. disini juga ada penginapannya, jadi paket komplit
review_translated_text: The place is very comfortable, beautiful, the owner is also very friendly. The menu is really delicious... there is also accommodation here, so its a complete package

review_text: Cute mini cafe, specialized in various coffee brew! The staffs are seriously kind and friendly. One of the best experience to ever have in Jogja.
Very good coffee, great hospitality. One of the best coffee in Yogyakarta, keep the good work!!! i like this coffee shop because not really crowded and every food is good too

Nice coffee place next to the Sultans Palace. I had a Kopi Warang and a Donut, the latter was done freshly for me and was pretty tasty! Both for a fair price of 38.000 IDR! While the place looks nice, its situated right next to a small, but busy street, so its quite nosy. Staff spoke English and the donut was his suggestion, though it was their cheapest snack. Thanks for not trying to screw another Westerner!
This coffee shop is designed in traditional style and it feels relaxing and slow inside. I like their coffee Parking: They also have a few parking space for cars
Tempatnya asik untuk ngopi, ngobrol santai & bernostalgia dengan teman lama. Servernya juga ramah-ramah. Kopinya enak.
review_translated_text: Its a cool place to drink coffee, chat casually & reminisce with old friends. The server is also friendly. The coffee is delicious.

review_text: Delicious coffee, nice place and very nice people.
review_translated_text: Heerlijke koffie, leuke plek en zeer aardige mensen.

review_text: The food is good, the coffee is excellent.

Tempatnya nyaman banget, kecil & mungil tapi worth it. Banyak spot buat foto, tentunya instagramable & estetik vintage gitu. Makanannya ala-ala bule, engga ada nasi jadi penggantinya roti aja. Tapi ternyata cukup bikin kenyang. Kemarin cobain Uncle Bob & Chicken Rhapsody rasanya enakk, scramble eggnya nagih!! Nyobain juga Shaken Tea Tropical & Spring rasanya unik & enak juga. Intinya recommended buat kesini guyss, mudah dijangkau karna ditengah kota & deket keraton
review_translated_text: The place is really comfortable, small & tiny but worth it. Lots of spots for photos, of course instagrammable & with a vintage aesthetic. The food is Caucasian style, there is no rice so just bread is substituted. But it turns out its enough to fill you up. Yesterday I tried Uncle Bob & Chicken Rhapsody it tasted delicious, the scramble eggs were addictive!! Also try Shaken Tea Tropical & Spring it tastes unique & delicious too. In essence, its recommended to come here guys, its easy to reach because its in the middle of the city & near the palace

review_text: We loved this place ! A real little bubble of oxygen in Yogyakarta! The waiter is adorable, speaks very good English and the atmosphere is very calming. We recommend it 100%!
Halal Nice

Makanan dan minuman enak. Sayang tempatnya kecil dan parkiran sulit Dietary restrictions: Menunya ada daging tanpa karbo Parking: Tempat parkir untuk motor tersedia didepan cafe. Namun untuk mobil hanya dipinggiran jalan dan tidak ada tukang parkirnya
review_translated_text: Delicious food and drinks. review_text: Bagus banget dan cozy, kalau ga hujan asik banget. Anak kecilnya dikasih cookies gratis dan mainan, jadi betah banget.
review_translated_text: Very nice and cozy, if it doesnt rain its really cool. The little ones were given free cookies and toys, so they really felt at home.

review_text: Melipir ke sini krn karena dekat dari alun2, bisa jalan kaki. Tempatnya adem di tengah panasnya Jogja. Di sini yang enak suasananya, tenang, adem, aesthetic. Untuk minuman saya rasa standar cafe/coffee shop. Krn saya suka kopi, menurut saya enak kopinya. Mas baristanya ramah.
review_translated_text: Came here because its close to the main square, you can walk. The place is cool in the heat of Jogja. The atmosphere here is nice, calm, cool, aesthetic. For drinks, I think its standard cafe/coffee shop. Because I like coffee, I think the coffee is delicious. The barista is friendly.

review_text: baristanya sudah menghafal ketika 2x kunjungan jadi tidak perlu sebutkan mau pesan apa sudah di offering duluan. Kopi Susu Regal ya mas? gitu katanya. Tempatnya kecil tapi nyaman untuk ngobrol.
review_translated_text: The barista has already memorized it during two visits so theres no need to mention what you want to order or what has been offered first. Regal Milk Coffee, bro? thats what he said. The place is small but comfortable for chatting.

review_translated_text: I accidentally passed by and it turns out the vibes of the coffee shop are really good... the taste of the coffee is also great...

review_text: Kesini random, dan first time. Ga nyangka ada coffee shop yang vibesnya relaxing+private gini. Kursinya gak banyak, nyaman buat ngobrol sama temen2, apalagi posisinya gak di jalan rame. Pesen salted caramel biscoff, mesen ini karna rekomendasi baristany. Buat yg suka manis2, bisa ini. Pesen juga shaken espresso. Light + fresh. Kesini pas siang2, ga kerasa sumuk karna sekeliling banyak pohon+tanaman. Kayaknya lebih asik kalo kesini malem.
review_translated_text: Came here randomly, and first time. I didnt expect there to be a coffee shop with a relaxing + private vibe like this. There arent many seats, its comfortable for chatting with friends, especially since its not on a busy street. Ordered salted caramel biscoff, ordered this because of the baristans recommendation. For those who like sweets, you can do this. Also order an espresso shaken. Light + fresh. Come here in the afternoon, it doesnt feel like its too crowded because there are lots of trees and plants around. It seems like its more fun to come here at night.

review_text: Very pleasant !
review_translated_text: Tres agreable !

review_text: Iiii ini hidden gem yang aku temuin secara ga sengaja. Kayaknya di dalemnya ada guest housenya juga ya. Pelayanannya ramah dan cepet, menu-menunya juga enak. Harga standard sih. Suasananya enak, bukan tipikal yg spacious cafe gitu ya, tapi nyaman. Wangi juga gitu loh pas masuk cafenya, kayak wangi bunga sedap malam. Lokasinya juga ada di tengah kota.
review_translated_text: Iiii this is a hidden gem that I found by accident. It seems like theres a guest house inside too. The service is friendly and fast, the menu is also delicious. The price is standard. The atmosphere is nice, not the typical spacious cafe, but comfortable. It also smells like that when you enter the cafe, like the scent of tuberose flowers. The location is also in the city center.

review_text: Tempat adem semilir & aesthetic, staff ramah, makanan enak, harga masuk akal. Selalu rame.
review_translated_text: Cool, breezy & aesthetic place, friendly staff, delicious food, reasonable prices. Always busy.

review_text: Excellent friendly spot to spend sometime with a coffee drink on a hot day.
Simple, cozy, and nice place

Suddenly visit sih ini. Meeting yang kepagian. Akhirnya ke Sapulu! Ternyata disini sudah buka dari jam 7 pagi. Menunya lebih ke western. Tapi semuanya enak! Menurut aku, tempat ini kurang oke kalau untuk nongkrong lama. Karena tempatnya relatif kecil dan kebanyakan orang yang kesini ya untuk kerja sepertinya (karena membawa laptop). Tapi seru sih. Definisi menikmati Jogja, kerja dari cafe, sambil slow living Notes: - Bisa payment dengan QRIS - Tidak ada retribusi parkir - Ada Resort di bagian belakang cafe ini Enjoy! Semoga terbantu!
review_translated_text: Suddenly visit here. Early meeting. Finally to Sapulu! It turns out its been open here since 7 am. The menu is more western. But everything is delicious! In my opinion, this place is not good for hanging out for a long time. Because the place is relatively small and most people come here for work, apparently (because they bring laptops). But its fun. The definition of enjoying Jogja, working from a cafe, while slow living Notes: - Can pay with QRIS - There are no parking fees - There is a Resort at the back of this cafe Enjoy! Hope this helps!

review_text: Random ke sini sama anak dan suami, ternyata tempatnya lucu, pengunjungnya kebanyakan bule. Di sini juga ada airbnbnya. Staffnya sangat ramah, hospitalitynya juara, mungkin karena standarnya tinggi ya, beda dengan kafe2 lain yg kebanyakan dikunjungi warga lokal. Staff sangat atentif terhadap kebutuhan kami, apalagi kami membawa anak balita. Mulai dari ditawarkan meja yg lebih luas, diambilkan peralatan makan karena lihat kami sharing makanan. Porsi makanannya cukup banyak, jd anak saya tidak bisa menghabiskan makanan sendirian. Ownernya juga sangat humble dan ramah menyapa kami. Anak saya diberi mainan. Selain itu, saya juga melihat ownernya memberikan minuman hangat secara cuma2 untuk lansia yg berjualan kayu.
review_translated_text: Randomly came here with my children and husband, it turns out the place is cute, the visitors are mostly foreigners. There is also an Airbnb here. The staff are very friendly, the hospitality is top notch, maybe because the standards are high, different from other cafes which are mostly visited by local residents. The staff was very attentive to our needs, especially when we brought a toddler. Starting from being offered a wider table, eating utensils being taken because they saw us sharing food. The food portions are quite large, so my child cant finish the food alone. The owner is also very humble and friendly in greeting us. My child was given a toy. Apart from that, I also saw the owner giving free hot drinks to elderly people who sell wood.

review_text: Went to had lunch hoping their meals will be as great as the Bale Raos just to see its not (sorry to say). But again, it was a good experience for me.

German tourists (couple): Delicious food, a bit too spicy for my palate. Vegetarian alternatives upon request. Long wait for the food (40 minutes). Great ambience and mini tour of the Sultans brothers premises. Vegetarian options: Simply state that you want vegetarian food, then swap the meat side dish for tofu or other soy dishes.

Vegetarian options: einfach angeben, dass vegetarisch gewunscht ist, dann tauschen sie die Fleischbeilage in Tofu oder andere Sojagerichte.

review_text: Terrific food, terrific service, great environment. Having tried the restaurant linked to the palace, I thought this was tastier, with better ventilation and  no flies! Gentle gamelan music in the air, birdsong from burung kuku and other songbirds and the gentle December breeze made it really pleasant. I enjoyed my orange juice, with fresh lime accents! It was so good I had to go for seconds and then the nasi kuning was super tasty with impeccably made side dishes. Each one bursting with flavor and a good complement for the meal. Loved it! We also got their version of coconut rice, and a super yummy braised beef short rib with fried rice! Not to mention to super fresh and tasty tahu telur. Mmm

review_text: Resto ini sepertinya usaha keluarga. Tempatnya pun merupakan rumah keluarga Gusti Joyokusumo (adik kandung Sri Sultan HB X). Berkunjung ke sini saat malam hari, dan bertepatan menghadiri HUT salah satu OKP di Jogja. Makanan yang disajikan enak. Pelayanan ramah. Suasana di sini sangat kental dengan kebudayaan Jawa baik itu bangunan, kuliner, cerita, benda peninggalan, hingga terdengar alunan gamelan khas Jogja. Terdapat banyak foto di dinding yang berisi foto keluarga Gusti Joyo, HB X, dan bahkan keluarga keraton lainnya. Was a nice experience in Gadri Resto.
review_translated_text: This restaurant seems to be a family business. The place is also the family home of Gusti Joyokusumo (the younger brother of Sri Sultan HB Visited here at night, and coincided with attending the anniversary of one of the OKPs in Jogja. The food served is delicious. Friendly service. The atmosphere here is very thick with Javanese culture, including buildings, culinary delights, stories, heritage objects, and even the sounds of typical Jogja gamelan. There are many photos on the walls containing photos of the Gusti Joyo family, HB X, and even other palace families. Was a nice experience in Gadri Resto.

review_text: We ordered a salad, it looked like decorative vegetables, it was so tiny! The vegetables were dried, it was obvious that they had been cut up and then left in the fridge for at least the day before. There was more sauce than vegetables, and the sauce was horrible: pure mayonnaise with melted butter! The chicken we ordered was extremely dry, and we could count the fries that came with it. And I cant even say that the best was the drink, because the sprite didnt even have any gas... in short, we dont recommend it at all

Il y avait plus de sauce que de legumes, et la sauce etait horrible : de la mayonnaise pure avec du beurre fondu ! Le poulet quon a commande etait archi sec, et on pouvait compter les frites qui laccompagnaient. review_text: Perched atop the ibis Styles Yogyakarta, D  Skybar offers a breathtaking panoramic view of the cityscape, making it the perfect spot for a memorable evening out. As I ascended to the rooftop venue, I was immediately captivated by the vibrant ambiance and stylish decor, setting the stage for an unforgettable experience. Once seated, I couldn t help but marvel at the sweeping vistas of Yogyakarta spread out before me. The skyline glowed with the warm hues of sunset, casting a magical spell over the bustling city below. It was the ideal backdrop for savoring a refreshing cocktail and soaking in the lively atmosphere. Speaking of cocktails, D  Skybar boasts an extensive menu of handcrafted drinks, each concoction expertly crafted to perfection. From classic favorites to innovative twists, there was something to suit every palate. I opted for their signature Skytini, a delightful blend of tropical flavors that perfectly complemented the balmy evening air. While the drinks were undoubtedly the star of the show, D  Skybar also offers a tempting selection of small bites and appetizers to accompany your libations. From crispy calamari to savory sliders, each dish was expertly prepared and bursting with flavor, adding an extra layer of indulgence to the experience. One aspect that truly stood out to me was the impeccable service provided by the attentive staff. Despite the bustling atmosphere, the staff remained attentive and personable, ensuring that every guest felt welcomed and well taken care of throughout the evening. Overall, my experience at D  Skybar @ ibis Styles Yogyakarta was nothing short of spectacular. Whether you re looking for a romantic date night spot or a chic venue to unwind with friends, D  Skybar offers an unparalleled experience that is sure to leave a lasting impression.

review_text: Went there around 1pm and no-one was at the bar. Waited around a while and had to go downstairs to the hotel reception to ask them if the rooftop restaurant was open (it was) and for them to send someone up to provide a menu and take our order. Once the waiter had arrived though, service was very good. Food was pretty decent and it was nice having a rooftop view of the Yogakarta town. Mushroom soup was yummy, but its a small dish so definitely consider it a side dish and not a main. Spring rolls were great as well - Id recommend that as a good side dish too. Going here for lunch was actually very good since it was very quiet - this seems to be a popular evening place as well if you want night time busy vibes instead though. The only reason I put this at 4 star is because no-one is actually attending the bar once it opens for lunch and I had to prompt reception to send someone up.

review_text: Kuliner khas Gunungkidul ini berada di jalan Semanu, tepatnya di seberang kantor desa Semanu. Area parkir cukup luas, tempatnya bersih, kapasitas tempat duduk cukup banyak. Kalian dapat pesan menu sesuai selera atau bentuk paket. Menu paket terdiri dari sayur tempe lombok ijo, daun pepaya, daging sapi, babad, iso, wader, ayam goreng, trancam, brongkos dan sego abang. Seperti layaknya di rumah makan padang, untuk makanan yang masih utuh tidak disentuh tidak dihitung bayar. Tapi kalo sudah dimakan, meskipun tidak habis tetap dihitung satu porsi ya. Untuk rasa kita kasih dua jempol, sayur tempenya enak, pedesnya pas, daging/iso/babat nya empuk, wader crispynya gurih dan nasi merahnya pulen. Untuk harga standart, relatif terjangkau. Kecuali untuk snack/camilan, baiknya kalian tanya dulu harganya biar nggak kaget dan terheran-heran. Seperti kita... . Semoga bisa jadi masukan...
review_translated_text: This typical Gunungkidul culinary delight is on Jalan Semanu, precisely opposite the Semanu village office. The parking area is quite large, the place is clean, there is quite a lot of seating capacity. You can order a menu according to your taste or form a package. The package menu consists of green Lombok tempeh, papaya leaves, beef, babad, iso, wader, fried chicken, trancam, brongkos and sego abang. Just like in Padang restaurants, food that is still intact and untouched does not count towards payment. But if youve eaten it, even if you dont finish it, it still counts as one portion. For the taste, we give it two thumbs up, the tempe vegetables are delicious, the spicy is just right, the meat/iso/tripe is tender, the wader is crispy and delicious and the red rice is fluffy. For standard prices, it is relatively affordable. Except for snacks/snacks, its a good idea to ask the price first so you dont get shocked or surprised. Like us... . review_text: Terletak di sebuah sudut yang bersejarah dekat Alun-Alun Selatan dan Pojok Beteng Wetan, tersembunyi permata kecil yang memanjakan penikmat kopi. Tempat ini, meski mungil, menawarkan sebuah oase kecil yang sejuk dan nyaman, cocok untuk melepas penat atau sekadar menikmati hari. Segelas americano dingin yang mereka sajikan bukan sekedar hitam dan pahit, melainkan sebuah simfoni yang membangkitkan semangat dengan setiap tegukan. Menemani percakapan tanpa akhir para kawan kawan lamaku. Tak kalah menggugah selera, pisang goreng yang disajikan lembut di dalam, menciptakan harmoni rasa yang sempurna saat disantap bersama kopi. Meskipun tempat ini menawarkan pengalaman yang istimewa, para pengunjung harus memperhatikan bahwa area parkir cukup terbatas. Sebuah tantangan kecil yang patut dipertimbangkan bagi mereka yang mengendarai kendaraan besar. Namun, bagi pejalan kaki atau pengguna kendaraan kecil, lokasi ini adalah pilihan yang tepat untuk menghabiskan waktu santai di akhir pekan atau setelah hari kerja yang panjang. Singkatnya, jika kita mencari tempat yang menawarkan kedamaian di tengah kota dengan sajian yang memanjakan lidah, tempat ini layak menjadi pilihan.
review_translated_text: Located in a historic corner near Alun-Alun Selatan and Pojok Beteng Wetan, there is a hidden little gem that will delight coffee lovers. This place, although small, offers a cool and comfortable little oasis, perfect for unwinding or just enjoying the day. The glass of cold americano they serve is not just black and bitter, but a symphony that lifts the spirits with every sip. Accompanying the endless conversations of my old friends. No less appetizing, the fried bananas served are soft on the inside, creating a perfect harmony of taste when eaten with coffee. Although this place offers a special experience, visitors should note that the parking area is quite limited. A small challenge worth considering for those driving large vehicles. However, for pedestrians or small vehicle users, this location is the right choice to spend relaxing time on the weekend or after a long work day. In short, if we are looking for a place that offers peace in the middle of the city with dishes that pamper the taste buds, this place is worthy of being the choice.

Suasana cafe yang adem, serasa makan di rumah sendiri. Pelayanan cepat dan ramah. Harga sangat terjangkau. Bagi kalian yg berkunjung ke Jogja jangan lupa mampir kesini ya.

Meja juga langsung gercep dibersihkan dengan cairan pembersih begitu pelanggan sudah selesai dan pulang sehingga kebersihan terjaga. Kamar mandinya pun bersih dan estetik, bahkan disediakan buku juga di toilet haha. Wastafel juga bersih banget dan disediakan sabun cuci tangan juga tisu. Tidak ada bayar parkir! The food and drinks are also delicious, I just tried the iced americano and onion rings. As for the price, its not really cheap but its not really expensive either, its still the standard for coffeeshops in general... 20k or so. Tables are also quickly cleaned with cleaning fluid once the customer has finished and gone home so that cleanliness is maintained. The bathroom is clean and aesthetic, there are even books provided in the toilet haha. The sink is also very clean and hand washing soap and tissues are provided. No pay for parking! I like this hehe. Oh yes, but parking the car is a bit difficult.

review_text: Such a nice place and a nice owner

The meals are simple and delicious, and the interior decoration is also cute. You can feel the owners personal ingenuity  I got sunburned when I was in Yogyakarta, and it was not easy to find aloe vera in the local store. After asking the owner, he cut several pieces from the garden directly for me. My friends and I    we felt well taken care of, these kind and warm locals are one of the lovely memories in Yogyakarta

Great local breakfast!! The boss was very friendly and efficient and I was able to get everything I was looking for at a more than fair price! You can find both savory and sweet options: pressed fruit juices, spiced teas (local drink in Yogyakarta), excellent +++ fruit-filled pancakes, fruit-yogurt-granola bowls, as well as savory dishes from same kind as those found almost everywhere: nasi goreng, noodles etc. Each item costs around 25,000 rp, so with a hearty breakfast you can easily get by for 100,000 rp As a bonus, the room where we eat is rather pretty: wooded, surrounded by a garden imitating a small jungle and in a small street therefore quite quiet, and filled with paintings that the owner paints himself, which is everything also in the atmosphere of Yogyakarta, the  artist city of Indonesia
review_translated_text: Super petit-dejeuner local !! Le patron etait tres sympa et efficace et jai pu avoir tout ce que je cherchais a un prix plus que correct ! Vous pourrez trouver du sale comme du sucre : des jus de fruits presses, des thes aux epices (boisson locale a Yogyakarta), des crepes fourrees aux fruits excellentes +++, des bowls fruit-yaourt-granola, ainsi que des plats sales du meme genre que ceux quon trouve un peu partout : nasi goreng, nouilles etc. Chaque article coute environ 25000 rp, ce qui fait quavec un copieux petit dejeuner on peut sen sortir facilement pour 100000 rp En prime, la salle ou lon mange est plutot jolie : boisee, entouree dun jardin imitant une petite jungle et dans une petite rue donc assez calme, et remplie de tableaux que le patron peint lui-meme, ce qui est tout a fait dans lambiance de Yogyakarta egalement, la ville dartistes dIndonesie

review_text: Very nice location, fair prices, good service

review_text: Such a nice place and a nice owner

The meals are simple and delicious, and the interior decoration is also cute. You can feel the owners personal ingenuity  I got sunburned when I was in Yogyakarta, and it was not easy to find aloe vera in the local store. After asking the owner, he cut several pieces from the garden directly for me. My friends and I    we felt well taken care of, these kind and warm locals are one of the lovely memories in Yogyakarta

Great local breakfast!! The boss was very friendly and efficient and I was able to get everything I was looking for at a more than fair price! You can find both savory and sweet options: pressed fruit juices, spiced teas (local drink in Yogyakarta), excellent +++ fruit-filled pancakes, fruit-yogurt-granola bowls, as well as savory dishes from same kind as those found almost everywhere: nasi goreng, noodles etc. Each item costs around 25,000 rp, so with a hearty breakfast you can easily get by for 100,000 rp As a bonus, the room where we eat is rather pretty: wooded, surrounded by a garden imitating a small jungle and in a small street therefore quite quiet, and filled with paintings that the owner paints himself, which is everything also in the atmosphere of Yogyakarta, the  artist city of Indonesia
review_translated_text: Super petit-dejeuner local !! Le patron etait tres sympa et efficace et jai pu avoir tout ce que je cherchais a un prix plus que correct ! Vous pourrez trouver du sale comme du sucre : des jus de fruits presses, des thes aux epices (boisson locale a Yogyakarta), des crepes fourrees aux fruits excellentes +++, des bowls fruit-yaourt-granola, ainsi que des plats sales du meme genre que ceux quon trouve un peu partout : nasi goreng, nouilles etc. Chaque article coute environ 25000 rp, ce qui fait quavec un copieux petit dejeuner on peut sen sortir facilement pour 100000 rp En prime, la salle ou lon mange est plutot jolie : boisee, entouree dun jardin imitant une petite jungle et dans une petite rue donc assez calme, et remplie de tableaux que le patron peint lui-meme, ce qui est tout a fait dans lambiance de Yogyakarta egalement, la ville dartistes dIndonesie

review_translated_text: As the name suggests, it is located at the terminal which is provided as a parking area for tourist buses going to Malioboro. Malioboros magnetism is truly extraordinary, so many parking lots have been built around it. Nice atmosphere, strategic location, concept of a snack place with lots of choices. The coffee shop is also no less interesting to try enjoying Papuan coffee, the benches are varied, some are made from drums. At night there is live music and you can have a good time. Unfortunately toilets and hand washing facilities are not available at the top, you have to go down quite a flight of stairs or go down via a motorized vehicle route. Many motorbikes go to the top while cars just get to the bottom In front of it there is a gym for practicing bukahai and boxing

review_text: Untuk venue sih oke ya.. Tapi untuk makanan kalau ga ada bintang akan saya pilih yang tidak ada bintang deh.. Makanannya is absolutely ZONK atau NOL BESAR dengan harga yang OVER PRICE untuk ukuran di Yogyakarta. Dan masaknya lama, kami harus menunggu 45 menit Pesan paket ikan bakar dapatnya ikan bakar dengan ukuran yang tipis dan amat sangat amis, keras serta tidak dapat dimakan. Utk kangkungnya overcooked sampai warnanya berubah jadi coklat. Saya juga pesan bakwan jagung yang aesthetic banget sampai harus di cetak segala tapi dengan persentase jagung 30% dan tepung 70%. Dan saya pesan juga tahu sutra goreng yg saat datang sudah dingin.. Pokoknya semua makanan yang diberikan ke saya sudah dingin semua dari nasi, cah kangkung, ikan bakar (bukan ikan kalau saya bilang sih tapi cenderung ke potongan ikan), bakwan jagung dan tahu sutra goreng.. Serta manajemen harus mentraining ulang seluruh karyawan nya untuk lebih ramah melayani customer. Dan tidak perlu untuk di wrap itu makanan biarkan customer merasakan aroma masakannya. Dan untuk yang memberikan       anda yakin untuk memberikannya? Jangan malu untuk memberikan penilaian yang jujur Wheelchair accessibility: Tidak ada
review_translated_text: As for the venue, its okay.. But for the food, if there are no stars, I will choose the one without stars.. The food is absolutely ZONK or ZERO BIG with prices that are OVER PRICE for Yogyakarta. And it took a long time to cook, we had to wait 45 minutes Order a grilled fish package and get grilled fish that is thin and very fishy, hard and inedible. For the kale, overcook until the color turns brown. I also ordered corn bakwan which was so aesthetic that I had to print everything but with a percentage of 30% corn and 70% flour. And I also ordered fried silken tofu which when it arrived was already cold... Basically all the food that was given to me was cold, everything from rice, cah kale, grilled fish (not fish if I say so but tending to pieces of fish), corn fritters and tofu. fried silk.. And management must retrain all its employees to be more friendly in serving customers. And there is no need to wrap the food, let customers feel the aroma of the food. And for those who give       are you sure to give it? Dont be shy about giving an honest assessment Wheelchair accessibility: There isnt any

As for the vibe, this is indeed suitable for gatherings of many people, such as reunions, because it is very wide and has lots of places. In my opinion, the indoor space is a bit dark during the day and quite quiet. But the outdoor space is fun, relaxed and has a gentle breeze. It seems like this place is even more fun at night. review_text: Tempat nongkrong dekat kampus UMY yang harganya cukup affordable, tempatnya asik untuk nongkrong sore ke malam hari, dalamnya ada area terbuka juga. Agak kurang cocok jika panas dan hujan, wifi tidak terlalu cepat juga, ya tempatnya emang cocoknya untuk nongkrong bareng.. Masuk, pesan melalui kasir, menunya sudah tercantum dipapan menu belakang kasir, jika dirasa butuh bawa menu ke meja, bilang aja karena disediakan juga. Jika sudah tinggal bayar dan tinggal tunggu pesanannya datang, oh ya pembayaran bisa juga lewat QRIS. Kemarin nongkrong memang pesan yang non-coffee, untuk siberinya enak rasanya seperti yogurt dan cukup pas di lidah. Untuk taronya juga cukup, walaupun rasanya masih kalah dengan salah satu merk minuman. Untuk mendoan, sosis, dan pisang gorengnya enak, cukup worth it dengan harga yang pas Pelayanan perlu ditingkatkan kembali, tidak ada ramah-ramahnya sama sekali, terkesan jutek dan crew belakang kalau ngomong teriak-teriak walaupun saat kesitu hujan, tapi setelah hujan berhenti tetep aja teriak teriak. Pelayanan yang cukup ramah cuma mba mba yg agak kecil, berhijab, yang mengantarkan makanan. Harga cukup terjangkau, cuma sekitaran 15ribuan saja dan variasi menunya cukup banyak. Akses cukup gampang karena berdekatan dengan jalan wates, tinggal masuk sedikit yang notabenya jalannya masih aspal juga. Parkiran cukup luas untuk mobil dan motor tidak perlu khawatir.
review_translated_text: A place to hang out near the UMY campus with quite affordable prices, a cool place to hang out in the afternoon or evening, inside there is an open area too. Its a bit unsuitable if its hot and rainy, the wifi isnt very fast either, so its really a suitable place to hang out together... Enter, order via the cashier, the menu is listed on the menu board behind the cashier, if you feel you need to bring the menu to the table, just say so because it is provided too. If you have already paid and just wait for the order to arrive, oh yes, you can also pay via QRIS. Yesterday, when I was hanging out, I ordered non-coffee, the Siberian tasted delicious like yogurt and was quite right on the tongue. The taro is also sufficient, although the taste is still inferior to one of the drink brands. The mendoan, sausages and fried banana are delicious, quite worth it for the right price The service needs to be improved again, there is no friendliness at all, it seems rude and the back crew are shouting when they talk even though it is raining there, but after the rain stops they are still shouting. The service was quite friendly, only a rather small lady, wearing a hijab, delivered the food. The price is quite affordable, only around 15 thousand and the menu variations are quite large. Access is quite easy because it is close to Jalan Wates, just go in a little and the road is still asphalt. Parking is large enough for cars and motorbikes, no need to worry.

review_translated_text: I knew about this place because I was passing by... finally tried it Its quite interesting because there are quite a lot of menu choices, today we tried rib soup, grilled ribs, rawon, beef nasgor, duck with spices, cah broccoli original and mendoan. To drink we tried ginger drink, fruit juice, chocolate milk and lemon tea. The food can be said to be okay, it has taste, the portions are right, the presentation is clean, and it cooks really quickly. The onion sauce is also very spicy but delicious! The drink menu is still so so, hehehe. This place isnt big but it can accommodate a lot of people, there are those on the floor, there are those at the dining table, there are tents, there are long tables and there are tables with more relaxed chairs. The place is clean, the waiters are responsive, parking is available too. There is a sink n bathroom. For a location far from the city, its still worth trying

review_text: Angkringan legendaris sejak 1962   Sekarang sudah dipegang oleh generasi ketiga. Awalnya dijalankan oleh Pak Mo, lalu Pak Jo, dan sekarang oleh Pak Bagus dan Bu Nining. Menu klasiknya ialah minuman sari dele tape. Cita rasa kriminya bikin terngiang-ngiang   Gorengannya juga enak2. Semua gorengan dan nasi dibuat oleh Bu Nining. Saat ini angkringan buka pk. 19.00 dan tutup sekitar pk. 00.30. Tapi bisa jadi lebih cepat jika pengunjung ramai. Tutup hari selasa ya
review_translated_text: Legendary angkringan since 1962   Now it is owned by the third generation. Initially run by Pak Mo, then Pak Jo, and now by Pak Bagus and Bu Nining. The classic menu is the dele tape cider drink. The creamy taste makes you remember   The fritters are also delicious. All the fried food and rice are made by Mrs. Nining. Currently the angkringan is open at 10 p.m. 19.00 and closes around 10 p.m. 00.30. But it could be faster if there are lots of visitors. Closed on Tuesdays OK

review_text: Tempat kebetulan lagi sepi di dalam. Ramenya malah di luar krn pas ada event panggung. Belom coba menu main course... Baru coba cemilan dan minuman. Rasanya cukup enak tapi biasa saja. The taste is quite good but ordinary. Sufficient place to take a break after walking for a long time at the mall. Service is quite friendly. There is a childrens play corner. There are chairs that are fully wooden and there are wooden ones with cushions. There are no soft sofa models or large tables. Dim lighting. Kid-friendliness: There is a corner for children to play. Slides, plastic houses.

place_name: Bangi Kopi, Sleman City Hall, Yogyakarta
review_text: Pesan makanan seperti tidak siap. Pelayanan sih oke, tapi yang kagetnya saya pesan mie udang benar benar ga ada rasanya, hanya seperti mie murahan yang dikasih cabai dan kuahnya sangat tawar. Ga sesuai dengan harga dan gambar di menu. Untuk Soto juga kurang banget seperti soto murahan, kuahnya bening dan isinya hanya bihun, ayam, telur setengah dan kubis. Menu penyetannya sih lumayan tapi cenderung biasa, poin bagusnya sambelnya enak. Maaf tidak bermaksud menjelekkan tapi hanya ungkapan kekecewaan saja. Bagusnya tempat ini ada indoor dan outdoor. Ada mini playground yg bikin anak saya cukup senang. Tapi untuk rasa makanan perlu ditingkatkan lagi. Rasanya kurang worth saja dengan harga segitu. Terimakasih sudah membaca. Tambahan, dulu kami pernah juga makan disitu, dan rasanya enak enak saja, entah kenapa sekarang menurun kualitasnya.
review_translated_text: Order food like its not ready. The service was okay, but what was surprising was that the shrimp noodles I ordered really had no taste, just like cheap noodles with chili added and the sauce was very bland. Doesnt match the prices and pictures on the menu. Soto is also not really like cheap soto, the soup is clear and the contents are only vermicelli, chicken, half an egg and cabbage. The setting menu is quite good but tends to be ordinary, the good point is that the sauce is delicious. Sorry, I dont mean to offend, but its just an expression of disappointment. The good thing is that this place is indoor and outdoor. There is a mini playground which makes my child quite happy. But the taste of the food needs to be improved. It just doesnt seem worth it at that price. Thanks for reading. Additionally, we used to eat there, and it was delicious, but somehow the quality has decreased now.

review_text: Datang sebelum waktu buka puasa. Makanan dan minuman banyak yang kosong. Pesan nasi goreng 2 porsi diinformasi nunggu 45 menit, dan kami setuju, tapi setelah nunggu sejam nasi goreng dateng cuma 1, sudah ditanyakan dan dibilang iya saya cek, ternyata saat pesanan lain dianter ke meja, ditanyakan lagi soal pesanan yg kurang masih disuruh nunggu untuk dicek, dan ternyata mereka bilang belum diinput di sistem. Kalau ga siap buka, mending jangan buka dulu.
review_translated_text: Come before breaking the fast. Many food and drinks are empty. Ordered 2 portions of fried rice, we were told that we would have to wait 45 minutes, and we agreed, but after waiting for an hour, only 1 fried rice came, we asked and were told yes, Ill check, it turned out that when another order was delivered to the table, we asked again about the missing order and were still told Waiting to check, and it turns out they said it hasnt been entered in the system. If youre not ready to open it, its better not to open it yet.

place_name: Bangi Kopi, Sleman City Hall, Yogyakarta
Bangi Kopi, Sleman City Hall, Yogyakarta
review_text: Sorry to say tp beneran kecewa bgt. Pas datang mau pesan ga langsung disamper sm pelayannya. Giliran pelayannya dateng dan sini tanya salah satu jenis menu, pelayan jawabnya kurang tahu karna katanya masih baru. Okelah gapapa. Setelah kelar pesan terus nunggu, lama bgt kok ga dianter2. Kami nunggu selama sekitar 45menit sampai akhirnya saya tanya lagi ke pelayan (yg berbeda dgn pelayan yg tdi melayani kami) ternyata pesanan kami tidak masuk ke daftar orderan. Pantesan lama bgt ga dianter2 pdhl yg baru dateng aja langsung dianter. Seketika langsung pulang saking keselnya. Kecewa bgt sih. Nunggu lama dan ga dapet apa2. Semoga segera diperbaiki dan ga keulang di customer lain.
review_translated_text: Sorry to say but really disappointed. When I came to order, the waiter didnt immediately approach me. It was the waiters turn to come and ask about one type of menu, the waiter answered dont know because he said it was still new. OK, thats fine. After finishing the order, I kept waiting, it took a long time, but it wasnt delivered. We waited for about 45 minutes until finally I asked the waiter again (who was different from the waiter who had served us) and it turned out that our order was not included in the order list. No wonder it didnt take so long to be delivered, even though those who had just arrived were immediately delivered. Instantly he went home because he was so annoyed. Im really disappointed. Waited a long time and got nothing. Hopefully it will be repaired soon and it wont happen again to other customers.

review_text: Rasa makanan tidak terlalu istimewa. Tapi minumannya saya suka (kami pesan fruit tea party). Pelayannya ramah. Lokasinya yang membuat kami mencoba makan siang di sini. Di tengah marlioboro yang panas terik dan ramai, tempat makan yang tenang jadi harapan kami. Sepertinya kami tidak memilih tempat yang tepat. Di tengah2 kami makan, tiba2 ada manajer (?) yang berteriak2 memarahi anak buahnya.. keras sekali hanya beberapa meter dari kami duduk. Seketika itu juga kenikmatan makan siang kami menguap..
review_translated_text: The taste of the food is not that special. But I like the drinks (we ordered fruit tea party). The waiter is friendly. The location made us try lunch here. In the middle of the sweltering and busy Marlioboro, a quiet place to eat is our hope. Looks like we didnt choose the right place. In the middle of us eating, suddenly there was a manager (?) who shouted and scolded his subordinates... very loudly just a few meters from where we were sitting. Instantly our enjoyment of lunch evaporated...

Kalo ke jogja, pas di Malioboro, silahkan mampir toko roti satu ini. Toko roti yang udah ada puluhan taun di Jogja, legendaris... jangan menilai dari tampilan luar ya, coba beli dan rasakan.. enak! Informasi terbaru, toko ini sekarang ada kafe nya. Minuman yang ditawarkan masih sebatas kopi (kopi hitam tubruk dan kopi susu rempah). Keduanya patut dicoba. Ampiran yang cocok untuk rehat sejenak ketika jalan-jalan di Malioboro.
review_translated_text: If you go to Jogja, right in Malioboro, please stop by this bakery. This bakery has been around for decades in Jogja, legendary... dont judge it by the outside appearance, try buying it and taste it... delicious! The latest information, this shop now has a cafe. The drinks offered are still limited to coffee (blended black coffee and spiced milk coffee). Both are worth a try. Ampiran is suitable for taking a short break when walking around Malioboro.

review_text: Kl Bandung ada Roti Sidodadi, kl Jogja ada Roti Djoen. Dua2nya favoritnya almh Ibu
review_translated_text: In Bandung there is Roti Sidodadi, in Jogja there is Roti Djoen. These two were my late mothers favorites

review_text: Salah satu toko roti legendaris di Yogyakarta yang sudah berdiri sejak sebelum Indonesia merdeka. Salah satu produk yang paling terkenal di Toko Roti Djoen ialah ontbijtjoek atau roti gandum hitam. Harganya Rp8.000 per buah ketika saya membeli di sini. Memang agak mahal, sih, untuk sepotong roti. Namun, itu bisa dipahami karena toko ini sudah punya nama besar dan terletak di kawasan yang sangat strategis: Jalan Malioboro. Tokonya bersih dan rapi, menempati sebuah bangunan tua di tepi jalan. Pelayanan bagus dan karyawannya ramah. Cocok untuk jadi tempat berburu buah tangan kalau harga tidak jadi masalah.
review_translated_text: One of the legendary bakeries in Yogyakarta which has been around since before Indonesias independence. One of the most famous products at Toko Roti Djoen is ontbijtjoek or rye bread. The price was IDR 8,000 per piece when I bought it here. Its a bit expensive, though, for a piece of bread. However, this is understandable because this shop already has a big name and is located in a very strategic area: Jalan Malioboro. The shop is clean and neat, occupies an old building on the side of the road. Good service and friendly employees. Suitable as a place to hunt for souvenirs if price is not an issue.

The bread is soft, the nastar cake is too, but theres not too much filling. For ginger lovers, try the ginger cake, its really strong Unfortunately I couldnt try the eclairs and other cakes because I came on Sunday and my father said to make it on weekdays only. Will come here again to try something else

review_text: Jogja dan kenangan, katanya seperti itu. Ada yg punya memorabilia sama tempat ini? Masuk ke sini itu spti kembali ke masa lalu tanpa perlu mesin waktu. Bangunan toko dan interiornya khas toko lawasan. Toko roti legendaris, produknya dikemas sederhana, tapi soal rasa boleh diadu. Aneka roti dg resep kuno masih punya pelanggan setia ditengah gempuran produk bakery yg beraneka ragam. Mau roti manis/gurih ada, tinggal pilih. Rasa roti spiku dan semacam nastarnya enak, manis gurih dan wangi. Harganya sangat terjangkau . Lokasi toko berada di dekat pecinan sekitar Ketandan, Malioboro, tak jauh dari tugu pecinan. Konon katanya, produk di sini itu unggul karna tidak pakai pengembang/pengawet, jadi secara tekstur beberapa rotinya agak bikin ekstra usaha buat ngunyahnya
review_translated_text: Jogja and memories, he said like that. Does anyone have memorabilia about this place? Entering here is like going back in time without needing a time machine. The shop building and interior are typical of an old shop. Legendary bakery, the products are packaged simply, but the taste is fine. Various breads with ancient recipes still have loyal customers amidst the onslaught of diverse bakery products. If you want sweet/savory bread, just choose. The taste of spiku bread and a kind of nastar is delicious, sweet, savory and fragrant. The price is very affordable. The location of the shop is near Chinatown around Ketandan, Malioboro, not far from the Chinatown monument. It is said that the product here is superior because it doesnt use leaveners/preservatives, so the texture of some of the bread makes it a little extra effort to chew.

review_text: Saat ke Jogya saya sempatkan mampir ke toko roti legendaris ini stlh sebelumnya sempat bimbang, krn waktu terbatas, antara ke toko roti modern atau legendaris ( di Jakarta bakery modern banyak ). Saya beli roti pisang coklat, kue ontbitjkoek, sus keju, sus isi daging ( krn yg isi vla yg memang favorit disini sdh habis ), amandel kacang tanah. Kue sus keju ternyata di dalamnya berisi potongan keju sementara yg daging berisi olahan daging spt kornet. Kulit sus nya enak sekali. Kombinasi mentega & telur yg digunakan membuat kulit sus ini paling enak diantara sus yg pernah saya beli tmsk dibanding bakery2 se tipe yg ada di Jakarta. Terbayang pasti sus vla nya enak. Ontbijtkoek nya cukup enak, no. 2 terenak setelah bakery legendaris langganan saya yg ada di Jakarta. Roti pisang coklatnya standard tapi pisang nya manis. Toko ini bukanya jam 11 shg agak repot juga menyediakan waktu kesini ditengah tujuan liburan ke Jogya ialah mengunjungi obyek2 wisata yg ada. Lokasinya di Jl. Malioboro sederet dengan pasar Bringharjo.
review_translated_text: When I went to Jogya, I had the chance to stop by this legendary bakery after previously being confused, because time was limited, between going to a modern or legendary bakery (in Jakarta there are lots of modern bakeries). I bought chocolate banana bread, ontbitjkoek cake, cheese eclairs, meat-filled eclairs (because the one filled with vla which is a favorite here has run out), peanut tonsils. It turns out that the cheese eclairs contain pieces of cheese while the meat ones contain processed meat such as corned beef. The eclair skin is really delicious. The combination of butter & eggs used makes this eclair the tastiest among the eclairs Ive ever bought, compared to other types of bakeries in Jakarta. I imagine the sus vla must be delicious. The ontbijtkoek is quite delicious, no. 2nd tastiest after the legendary bakery I frequent in Jakarta. The chocolate banana bread is standard but the banana is sweet. This shop opens at 11 oclock so its a bit of a hassle to find time to come here because the aim of your holiday in Jogya is to visit the existing tourist attractions. The location is on Jl. Malioboro is in a row with Bringharjo market.

review_text: Roti nya enak
review_translated_text: The bread is delicious

review_text: Toko Djoen since 1935. Toko roti legendaris Jogja. Kalau suka roti-roti jadul, bisa cobain ini. Enak dan harganya murah-murah. Roti tawar yang paling gede harganya cuma 20 ribu. Kalau mau fresh bread, bisa datang hari Senin, Kamis, dan Sabtu. Mereka baking di hari itu. Datang jam 1 atau 2 gitu masih kebagian roti yang anget-anget. Di sini ada roti-roti kecil, roti buaya, onbitjkoek (favoritku), kue sus, dan pastri juga. Kue susnya gede, ada isi daging, ada isi keju. Yang pastri ada isi pisang (favoritku) dan ayam. Untuk roti kecil2 lainnya ada rasa cokelat, nanas, kelapa (favoritku), pisang, kacang merah, kacang tanah, roti amandel, dll. Lokasinya di jl Malioboro, deket gerbang Ketandan, seberangnya Ramai Mall, sederetan sama Ramayana Mall. Parkirnya bisa di samping Ramayana. Yang ngelayanin Oma Pin langsung (generasi ke-2), usianya 87 tahun. Oma Pin dibantuin sama anak perempuannya juga sehari-harinya. Mereka manggang rotinya masih pakai oven yang jadul banget itu. Oven chamber segede kamar kos kayak tempat pemanggangan pizza gitu. Nyalainnya pakai solar. Nah, berhubung solar sekarang mahal dan susah nyarinya, itu jadi kendala di mereka juga. Kalau ke sini dilarisin ya gais, biar toko rotinya long last, soalnya legendaris banget nih. Nggak rela kalau sampai tutup
review_translated_text: Toko Djoen since 1935. Jogjas legendary bakery. If you like old school bread, you can try this. Its delicious and the price is cheap. The biggest plain bread only costs 20 thousand. If you want fresh bread, you can come Monday, Thursday and Saturday. They were baking that day. When we arrived at 1 or 2 oclock we still had some really hot bread. Here there are small breads, crocodile bread, onbitjkoek (my favorite), eclairs, and pastries too. The eclairs are big, have meat filling and cheese filling. The pastry contains banana (my favorite) and chicken. For other small breads, there are flavors of chocolate, pineapple, coconut (my favorite), banana, red bean, peanut, tonsil bread, etc. The location is on Jl Malioboro, near the Ketandan gate, opposite Ramai Mall, in the same row as Ramayana Mall. Parking can be next to Ramayana. The one who serves Oma Pin directly (2nd generation), she is 87 years old. Grandma Pin is also helped by her daughter on a daily basis. They still bake the bread using that really old school oven. The oven chamber is as big as a boarding room, like a pizza oven. Turn it on using diesel. Well, since diesel fuel is now expensive and hard to find, thats a problem for them too. If you come here, its a hit, guys, so the bakery shop has long last, because its really legendary. I dont want it to close

review_text: Lokasinya ada di pertokoan kiri jalan Malioboro, sebelum gerbang Pecinan Ketandan. Bakery kuno yang pilihan roti-rotinya juga klasik (cokelat, keju, daging, selai, tawar, dll). Harga under 15k/pcs buat yg roti satuannya. Isinya cukup banyak, terasa resep kunonya (wangi buttery kenceng, teksturnya bukan yg lembut banget kayak dikasih pelembut tapi). Kusuka yang isi cokelat karena isi cokelatnya yg berasa krenyes-krenyes (?) bukan selai kayak biasanya gitu.
review_translated_text: The location is at the left shop on Jalan Malioboro, before the Ketandan Chinatown gate. An ancient bakery with classic bread choices (chocolate, cheese, meat, jam, plain, etc.). Price under 15k/pcs for individual bread. Theres quite a lot of content, it feels like an old recipe (the strong buttery smell, the texture isnt really soft like if you had softened it). I like the chocolate filled ones because the chocolate filling tastes crunchy (?) instead of jam like usual.

review_text: Senin siang, di jalanan Malioboro yang sepi, terkerjut liat roti tawar yang menul menul baru matang ini. Tapi karena sedang travelling saya beli roti manis isi coklat saja, harganya 8000 rupiah dan enak banget :

review_translated_text: Bakery legend in Jogja, since the 30s. The types of bread are old school like oenbijtkoek, soes, crocodile bread, banana bread etc. Most like it with banana-chocolate sauce or ragout filling. The cakes are usually cooked from 13.00-15.00, still warm, the white bread is thick, fat, whole and hasnt been cut, you can ask to cut it at the same time. Back in the 80s, the donuts were thick and soft, but now it seems they dont make them anymore. You can park in the large Ketandan parking area, enter from the Ramayana, walk 150m and explore Ketandan Chinatown at the same time

For those visiting Jogja, dont forget to stop by.

review_text: Toko roti legendaris di Malioboro. Sudah melapak semenjak masa kolonial, Toko Djoen kondang akan roti pisangnya yg inuk biyanget. Memang, beberapa kali kesini dan mencecap beragam rotinya, tetap yg terbaik roti pisangnya. Terkahir kesini roti pisangnya dibanderol 7K/bungkus. Oh ya, selaiknya toko pastry, di sini pun tersedia beragam roti lain seperti roti kacang, roti nanas, obijtkoek, roti gambang dsb dsb hingga panganan ringan. Pelayanan dari pegawainya ramah dan cekatan. Oh ya, roti di sini pun senantiasa fresh, lho. Lokasi berada sederetan dg ruko dekat Ramayan Mall.
review_translated_text: Legendary bakery in Malioboro. Having been around since colonial times, Toko Djoen is famous for its banana bread which is inuk biyanget. Indeed, I have been here several times and tried various breads, but the banana bread is still the best. Lastly, the banana bread is priced at 7K/pack. Oh yes, like a pastry shop, there are also various other breads available here such as peanut bread, pineapple bread, obijtkoek, gambang bread, etc., and even light snacks. The service from the employees is friendly and agile. Oh yes, the bread here is always fresh, you know. The location is in a row with shophouses near Ramayan Mall.

The place is not far from the Kali Kuning bridge where the Jeep rides, it is on the side of the road with a fairly large billboard. Suggestions for the cook, maybe dont use too much flavoring for the soup, maam, its better to use real chicken broth to make it delicious. As for the mendoan, this is really mendoan, not tempe kemul, because it is half-fried, not until its crispy. Coming back? Of course!

review_text: Untuk tempat dengan konsep lawas, tempat ini cukup nyaman dan menenangkan. Terdapat pojok galeri yang menampilkan beberapa benda-benda jadul dan photo yang berisi silsilah raja-raja beberapa kerajaan, khususnya kerajaan di tengah pulau Jawa. Gerobak makanan dan minuman juga senada dengan konsep yang diusung. Sebagai catatan, hanya untuk dipertimbangkan, bukan untuk mendiskriminasi, pengelola tempat ini kristiani. Namun saya pun tetap merasa nyaman, atas keramahan pengelola.
review_translated_text: For a place with an old school concept, this place is quite comfortable and relaxing. There is a gallery corner which displays several old objects and photos containing the genealogy of the kings of several kingdoms, especially kingdoms in the middle of Java. Food and drink carts are also in line with the concept being promoted. For the record, just to be considerate, not to discriminate, the management of this place is Christian. However, I still felt comfortable, thanks to the friendliness of the manager.

Pertama kali ke sini yang paling terkesan adalah desain interiornya yang menurut saya mirip2 bali tapi juga mirip tradisional jawa. Tapi karena dipintu masuk ada semacam gapura, jadi atmosphere nya lebih ke Bali. Terus begitu, interiornya terlihat mahal2 wkwkwk... Meja dengan kayu tebal berkaki besi hollow, couch yang nyaman, dan ornamen2 lain Selain tempat duduk, ada juga lesehan... buat penggemar slenjeran kaki...ini cocok. Makanan, saya rasa standard selera masing-masing,.tapi menurutku worth the price. Posisi yang diapit air (kali kecil) menjadikan ambience alamnya jadi lebih kerasa, bisa jadi terapi buat saya yang lagi hectic Cobain
review_translated_text: The first time I came here, what impressed me the most was the interior design, which in my opinion resembled Bali but also resembled traditional Javanese. But because there is a kind of gate at the entrance, the atmosphere is more Balinese. And so, the interior looks expensive hahaha... Tables with thick wood with hollow iron legs, comfortable couches, and other ornaments Apart from seating, there is also a lesehan... for fans of leg stretching... this is suitable. The food, I think is standard to each individuals taste, but I think its worth the price. The position flanked by water (small river) makes the natural ambience more pronounced, it could be therapy for me who is hectic try it

review_text: Warung susu sapi murni yang diberi nama Kasuli (Kafe Susu Tuli) ini dikelola oleh seorang tuna rungu (tuli). Dan memang beberapa pengunjung adalah teman2 tuli. Selain menikmati susu sapi murni kita juga bisa menikmati karya2 seni seperti lukisan dan fotografi yang semuanya hasil karya dari teman2 difabel. Disediakan juga air minum untuk kesehatan secara gratis. Air minum ini diolah setelah melewati proses penelitian sehingga aman untuk dikonsumsi.
review_translated_text: This pure cows milk stall, named Kasuli (Deaf Milk Cafe), is managed by a deaf person. And indeed some of the visitors were deaf friends. Apart from enjoying pure cows milk, we can also enjoy works of art such as paintings and photography, all of which are the work of friends with disabilities. Drinking water for health is also provided free of charge. This drinking water is processed after going through a research process so that it is safe for consumption.

review_text: Tempatnya benar2 sejuk. Vibes hutan bambu dengan udara yang menyegarkan. Nyampe sana sekitar jam 8 pagi, masih sepi dan menjadi pengunjung pertama. Makanan prasmanan belum siap. Yang tersedia baru minuman dan beberapa jenis camilan ( tempe mendoan, bakwan, dll). Pelayanan cukup ramah. Waktu penyajian makanan yang dipesan juga cukup cepat. Teh pocinya kentel dan segar. Camilan bakwan + cocolan kecap pedas juga lumayan enak. Harga masih sangat terjangkau. Tersedia tempat parkir yang luas. Cocok untuk tempat ngadem dan menyegarkan pikiran dari hiruk pikuk kota.
review_translated_text: The place is really cool. Bamboo forest vibes with refreshing air. Arrived there around 8 in the morning, it was still quiet and I was the first visitor. Buffet food is not ready. Only drinks and several types of snacks are available (tempeh mendoan, bakwan, etc.). Service is quite friendly. The serving time for the food ordered is also quite fast. The teapot is thick and fresh. The bakwan snack + spicy soy sauce dip is also quite delicious. Prices are still very affordable. Ample parking is available. Suitable for a place to relax and refresh your mind from the hustle and bustle of the city.

review_text: Untuk kesekian kalinya kemari, ada beberapa perubahan, dulu tersaji set prasmanan menu masakn nusantara (cenderung jawa) sperti sayur ndeso, mangut lele dan lain lain, namun sekarang berubah concept ala carte, pesan langsung dengn menu seperti pecel lele, nasi goreng, mie dan lain lain. untuk rasa cukup lumayan , hanya saja bihun goreng nya kebetulan saya dapat yang terlalu asin. untuk kopi susu otentik lokal tradisional. untuk harga, murah dan sangat terjangkau sebagai tempat santai, enak sekali, sejuk dan dingin alami pelohonan. terdapat beberapa spot foto alami dan arena atv untuk anak dan dewasa Untuk toilet, mungkin bs lebih sering dikontrol dan dibersihkan lantainya Untuk pelayanan lumayan, hanya kasir cowoknya yg agak jutek. mungkin lg kademen #jogjafoodstock #kulinerjogja #kulineryogya #jogjahits #kulinerjogjahits #kulinernusantara #yogyamakan #jogjamakan #makanjogja #makanyogya #reviewkuliner #makandijogja #voilajogja #riderskulineran #jogjastreetfood #jogjafoodhunter #kulinerkekinian #jajankekinian #kulinerlegendaris #makananviral #komentarkuliner #kuliner #ngopidijogja #kulinerbaru #kulinerkekinian
review_translated_text: For the umpteenth time here, there have been several changes, previously there was a set buffet menu of Indonesian dishes (tends to be Javanese) such as Ndeso vegetables, mangut lele and others, but now the concept has changed to ala carte, order directly with menus such as pecel lele, fried rice, noodles and so on. etc. The taste is quite good, its just that I happened to get the fried vermicelli which was too salty. for traditional local authentic milk coffee. for the price, cheap and very affordable as a relaxing place, very nice, cool and naturally cool. there are several natural photo spots and an ATV arena for children and adults For toilets, maybe the floors can be controlled and cleaned more often The service is decent, only the male cashier is a bit rude. maybe even a cadet #jogjafoodstock #culinaryjogja #kulineryogya #jogjahits #kulinerjogjahits #kulinernusantara #yogyamakan #jogjamakan #makanjogja #makanyogya #culinaryreview #makandijogja #voilajogja #riderskulineran #jogjastreetfood #jogjafoodhunter #kulinerkekinian #snackskekinian #culinerlegendaris #makananviral #kojenkuliner #culinary #ngopidijogja #new culinary #current culinary

review_text: If you are looking to get good food and drinks, then I dont recommend this place at all.  We waited for the food for more than an hour. And thats not complete,  they forgot our order and also told me that my order not available after an hour of waiting.   I guess if you are hungry you will pass out before you can eat. But if youre just looking for a place to sit down and rest then you can come here and only order a drink.. The place still acceptable to do that. The only thing you will like is the price is very cheap here. They also provide ATV rental if you want to play some Offroading at their track there.

review_translated_text: Taste : 5/5 Price : 5/5 Place : 5/5 Service: 5/5 (+) So far, the impression of this place is quite positive. In terms of price, it is very affordable, simple vegetable rice starts at 10 thousand, the prices for drinks and snacks are also really good. The place is spacious, cool and cool. The service is two thumbs up, the employees are sensitive when we need a roll of cable without asking. (-) Maybe the only lack of WiFi is that when I went there there was a problem, even though the area there had poor cellular network :(, as a result I had to take a break to play on my cell phone hehe. The food and drink menu wasnt as much as other restaurants and was quite simple. But once again its really good to visit here.

review_text: Tempat ini, Home Wok di Baciro, yang kini juga hadir di Jalan Kabupaten, menawarkan pengalaman yang hampir sama dengan cabang-cabangnya yang lain. Kebersihan tempat dan kenyamanan yang disediakan hampir tidak berbeda jauh, dengan AC yang bekerja baik dan suasana yang nyaman. Salah satu keunggulan tempat ini adalah keberadaan kamar mandi yang bersih, yang merupakan faktor penting dalam menjamin kenyamanan pengunjung. Namun, terdapat beberapa kekurangan yang perlu diperhatikan. Salah satunya adalah harga minuman dan makanan yang sedikit lebih tinggi dibandingkan tempat sejenis di sekitarnya. Dengan harga minuman di atas 15 ribu dan rata-rata makanan di kisaran 20-25 ribu, tempat ini mungkin kurang cocok bagi mereka yang mencari tempat dengan harga lebih terjangkau. Selain itu, kursi-kursi yang tersedia di tempat ini perlu diperbaiki karena kurang nyaman, mungkin dengan menambahkan bantal atau memperbarui kursi-kursi tersebut. Meskipun demikian, tempat ini tetap menawarkan suasana yang cukup menyenangkan untuk bekerja, dengan adanya hiburan tambahan seperti aneka mainan yang dapat menghibur pengunjung. Secara keseluruhan, Home Wok di Jalan Kabupaten adalah tempat yang layak untuk dikunjungi, terutama bagi mereka yang mencari suasana yang nyaman untuk bekerja atau sekadar bersantai. Meskipun memiliki beberapa kekurangan, kebersihan, kenyamanan, dan suasana yang menyenangkan masih menjadi keunggulan utamanya. Parking: Pinggir jalan parkir terbatas kalau bawa mobil Kid-friendliness: Ada mainan anak anaknya
review_translated_text: This place, Home Wok in Baciro, which is now also present on Jalan Kabupaten, offers almost the same experience as its other branches. The cleanliness of the place and the comfort provided are almost no different, with the AC working well and the atmosphere comfortable. One of the advantages of this place is the presence of clean bathrooms, which is an important factor in ensuring visitor comfort. However, there are several drawbacks that need to be noted. One of them is that the prices of drinks and food are slightly higher than similar places in the surrounding area. With drink prices above 15 thousand and the average meal in the range of 20-25 thousand, this place may not be suitable for those looking for a place with more affordable prices. Apart from that, the chairs available in this place need to be improved because they are not comfortable, perhaps by adding pillows or updating the chairs. However, this place still offers a pleasant atmosphere for working, with additional entertainment such as various toys that can entertain visitors. Overall, Home Wok on Jalan Regency is a place worth visiting, especially for those looking for a comfortable atmosphere to work or just relax. Even though it has several shortcomings, cleanliness, comfort and a pleasant atmosphere are still its main advantages. Parking: Roadside parking is limited if you bring a car Kid-friendliness: There are childrens toys

review_translated_text: I just ordered tea here because Jogja was cold and raining at that time. Its in the same building as the barbershop, women can also get their hair cut here as long as its a boys hairstyle hahaha. Its cheap and delicious here, but unfortunately the outdoor area is limited so theres no place outside, even though its fun watching people go by at night hehe. Mas, who is on guard, is also really funny with his girlfriend, when his girlfriend comes, hahaha, cute couple. There are snacks here too! Dont be afraid of being hungry, okay? :)

review_text: Namanya Movement coffe, tapi disini tempat Barbershop. Kesini cuma mau potong rambut aja jadi kurang tau kalau nongkrong nyaman atau tidak, untuk menu saya kurang tau juga. Tapi kalau mau potomg di sini harus Booking Order dulu, nggak bisa langsung potong. Saya kemaren dateng Booking Order dulu, setelah itu kalau sudah waktunya nanti di Whatsapp. Booking Order nya bisa langsung ke lokasi atau via Whatsapp. Kalo beli minuman sekalian potong, harga minumannya beda. Saya di kasih tau sama adminnya.
review_translated_text: Its called Movement Coffee, but this is a barbershop. I just came here to get a haircut so I dont know if hanging out is comfortable or not, I dont know about the menu either. But if you want to cut here you have to book an order first, you cant cut straight away. Yesterday I came to Book Order first, after that, when its time, Ill go to Whatsapp. Booking orders can be done directly at the location or via Whatsapp. If you buy a drink and cut it, the price of the drink is different. I was notified by the admin.

review_text: good place to chill out. fyi the name changed to  movement coffee . was craving for some burger but most stuff on the menu weren t available anymore. i only ordered hot peach lemon tea &original toast, both were okay.

Btw kalo lucky bisa dapet diskonan untuk pembelian tertentu. Karna kemaren pesen mix platter & coffee latte doang langsung dapet voucher diskon kopi 50%, cuma lupa sampe kapan event beginiannya berakhir sama S&K buat dapet voucher-nya. Kalo soal rasa kopi sayangnya bukan ahlinya, yg penting mah ngopi we sambil nongkrong.
review_translated_text: The prices are pocket friendly, almost all of the menu doesnt cost 20k, except for the burgers as far as I remember. The atmosphere is comfortable and you can drink coffee outdoors but the space is a bit limited. BTW, if youre lucky, you can get a discount on certain purchases. Because yesterday I ordered a mix platter & coffee latte and immediately got a 50% coffee discount voucher, I just forgot how long an event like this ends with the T&C for getting the voucher. When it comes to the taste of coffee, unfortunately Im not an expert, the important thing is drinking coffee while hanging out.

Im referring to the Special Iced Milk Coffee, the coffee tastes combined with the deliciousness of milk and palm sugar. Also try Kopi Bakar, brewed coffee which is served with roasted coffee topping - poured right before serving over a hot fire... Snacks to accompany coffee also vary from French fries, pempek, cassava cheese, maryam bread to mix platters. There is also a menu of delicious fried rice and Javanese noodles, Mrs. NYUS The price is quite affordable. Eat deliciously, drink deliciously without breaking the bank. review_translated_text: Came here after seeing content on IG. The place is quite deep into an alley but its not difficult to find. I came at night and the weather was very nice, fresh after the rain. The place is quite spacious, when I came here there were already many families eating. I ordered stir-fried firecrackers, satay koyor, and ribs soup. In my opinion, the stir-fried firecrackers and koyor satay are too sweet. Even if you eat it with rice, its still sweet. However, the texture of the koyor satay is a winner. If it didnt taste sweet, Id dare say this is the best koyor satay Ive ever eaten. The rib soup is tender, the broth is also delicious. In my opinion, the price is relatively cheap to bring the family to eat here.

review_text: Kalau kamu suka suasana sepi di tengah keriuhan pusat kota; cafe ini pilihan terbaik. Kami tidak sengaja menemukannya. Kamu bisa duduk dengan segelas kopi, beberapa halaman buku, atau layar laptop. Bagus juga kalau mau sekadar melamun. Kopi susu karamelnya enak, harga murah. Kedai kopi kecil ini tidak banyak aksesoris; tempelan-tempelan hiasan di setiap ruang. Semuanya sederhana saja. Sebuah bekas rumah tua yang disulap jadi kedai dengan kursi kursi yang pas, meja yang nyaman; semua memanggilmu untuk duduk beberapa waktu disini, dengan segelas kopi dan melihat hidup ya cuma gini gini.
review_translated_text: If you like a quiet atmosphere amidst the hustle and bustle of the city center; This cafe is the best choice. We stumbled upon it by accident. You can sit with a cup of coffee, a few pages of a book, or a laptop screen. Its also good if you want to just daydream. The caramel milk coffee is delicious, the price is cheap. This small coffee shop doesnt have many accessories; decorative hangings in every room. Its all simple. A former old house transformed into a shop with suitable chairs, comfortable tables; everyone is calling you to sit here for a while, with a cup of coffee and see life just like this.

review_text: Sebuah kafe rumahan yang nyaman sekali untuk berlama-lama di dalamnya. Lokasinya hanya sepelemparan batu dari Alun-Alun Selatan. Mungkin karena kafe baru, pelanggannya masih belum terlalu banyak. Pelayanannya luar biasa ramah. Saat datang pada sore hari sekitar jam 16.00, seorang pelayan yang sepertinya juga pemilik kafe menyambut dengan ceria dan bilang bahwa mereka baru saja buka hari Minggu itu karena ada acara keluarga sebelumnya. Waktu bertanya sudah berapa lama kafe ini berdiri, mbak yang melayani menjawab, Baru tiga bulan. Saya memesan choco latte, platter, dan roti bakar choco cheese. Rasa ketiga menu itu enak dan pas. Harganya pun pas di kantong dengan porsi yang lumayan mengenyangkan. Bahkan roti bakarnya tidak habis, padahal enak banget. Saya akan kembali lagi ke sini. Mungkin beberapa kali seminggu. Saya bahkan berkelakar dengan teman saya, Wah bisa nih jadi rumah kedua! Tempat yang cocok sekali untuk bekerja sambil laptopan atau hanya nongkrong/ngobrol bareng teman atau keluarga!
review_translated_text: A homely cafe that is very comfortable to linger in. The location is just a stones throw from South Square. Maybe because the cafe is new, there arent many customers yet. The service is extraordinarily friendly. When we arrived in the afternoon at around 16.00, a waiter who seemed to be the owner of the cafe greeted us cheerfully and said that they had just opened that Sunday because there was a family event beforehand. When asked how long this cafe had been around, the lady serving answered, Only three months. I ordered a choco latte, platter and choco cheese toast. The taste of the three menus was delicious and just right. The price is right on the pocket with portions that are quite filling. Even the toast wasnt finished, even though it was really delicious. I will come back here again. Maybe a few times a week. I even joked with my friend, Wow, this could be a second home! A perfect place to work on your laptop or just hang out/chat with friends or family!

review_text: Banyak banget varian jenis jajanannya. Jajanan yang dijual di sini ada takoyaki (dengan harga sepuluh ribu per porsinya), terus ada telur gulung (ada pilihan harga lima ribuan atau yang sepuluh ribuan), sosis bakar (harganya sepuluh ribu), ada minuman cokelat (yang original harganya enam ribu, sedangkan yang toping harganya delapan ribu). Selain cokelat, ada minuman berbagai rasa juga, yaitu rasa red velvet, taro, avocado, green tea, sama thai tea. Di sini harganya yang original delapan ribu, sedangkan yang bertoping sepuluh ribu. Oiya hampir lupa, di sini juga jual baby crab dengan harga sepuluh ribu per porsinya. Ada varian rasa original, saos jos, bbq, balado, keju, dan pedas. Overall cukup worth it buat jajan di sinisaos karena bisa beli banyak jenis jajanan cukup di satu tempat aja dan harganya juga standar. Kemarin ke sini beli takoyakinya aja sih. Seporsinya isi enam bulat dengan harga sepuluh ribu rupiah. Takoyakinya agak lembek, tapi mungkin itu karna masih panas dan kena saos. Next, mau nyobain jajanan yang lainnya
review_translated_text: There are so many different types of snacks. The snacks sold here are takoyaki (priced at ten thousand per portion), then there are egg rolls (there is a choice of five thousand or ten thousand), grilled sausages (priced at ten thousand), there are chocolate drinks (original ones cost six thousand, while the topping costs eight thousand). Apart from chocolate, there are drinks with various flavors too, namely red velvet, taro, avocado, green tea and Thai tea. Here the price for the original is eight thousand, while the one with the top is ten thousand. Oh yes, almost forgot, here they also sell baby crab for ten thousand per portion. There are original flavors, jos sauce, bbq, balado, cheese and spicy. Overall, its quite worth it for snacks at Sinisaos because you can buy many types of snacks in just one place and the prices are also standard. Yesterday I came here to buy takoyaki. A portion contains six rounds and costs ten thousand rupiah. The takoyaki was a bit soft, but maybe that was because it was still hot and covered in sauce. Next, I want to try other snacks

review_text: View & tempat nya asri banget.  Tapi maaf ya minuman & makanannya dibawah B.  Pisang goreng nya C- dari segi rasa & presentasi.  Jauh banget kalo dibandingkan dgn sebuah tempat yng terkenal.  Kemudian Kopi panas & Jahe panas nya juga lebih terasa ke air nya.    Pesan Soto tapi kuahnya berasa air bukan kaldu dan asin nya banget.  Dicoba di santap dgn nasi juga tetap asin banget.  Nasi nya juga tidak pulen.  Konsep nya open kitchen & karyawan nya bisa dilihat sedang makan di dalam dapur.   Mbak yng di kasir ramah & baik.
response_from_owner_text: Halo kak Sari, mohon maaf apabila menu layanan belum bisa memenuhi harapan kakak, kami akan terus lakukan perbaikan agar bisa memberikan yang lebih baik lagi. Terima kasih atas kunjungannya dan kami tunggu kedatangannya kembali
review_translated_text: The view & place is really beautiful. But sorry, the drinks & food are below B. The fried banana is C- in terms of taste & presentation. Its really far compared to a famous place. Then the hot coffee & hot ginger are also more pronounced in the water. Ordered Soto but the sauce tasted like water, not broth, and it was really salty. Tried it with rice and it was still very salty. The rice was also not fluffy. The concept is open kitchen & employees can be seen eating in the kitchen. The lady at the cashier is friendly & kind.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello Sis Sari, we apologize if the service menu cannot meet your expectations, we will continue to make improvements so that we can provide even better services. Thank you for visiting and we look forward to welcoming you back
