review_text: 30 Agustus 23/ Nasi kucing 5rb, tempe 1rb an, teh hangat 3rb. Nasi kucingnya agak mahal, tapi emang porsinya gede 1 mangkok nasi. Nasinya juga fresh dari magic com, diporsiin terus ditaruh di piringnya dan dikasih sambel teri. Selain sambel teri juga ada pilihan oseng oseng ati. Sambel terinya cukup enak, pedes gurih dengan teri yang nggak mengecewakan. Tempenya tipis, jadi 1rb itungannya agak mahal tapi ya sudahlah. Namanya juga harga angkringan di pusat wisata. Teh angetnya oke, standar. Tempatnya pas setelah gapura pertama alun alun dari arah 0km. Duduknya bisa di dalem lesehan agak luas, untuk di luar juga ada 1 meja kursi panjang gitu. Juga bisa di bangku trotoar 0km. Lumayan syahdu sih suasananya, berangkringan ria di 0km. Nggak ada wastafel, nggak ada tisu. Bayar harus tunai. Overall pretty good, a bit pricey tapi dapat dipahami untuk tempat wisata. Hitungannya masih lebih murah dari sebelah sebelahnya anyway. Bisa lah mampir kalau mau sok syahdu atau ngganjel perut dulu.
review_translated_text: 30 August 23/ Rice cat 5 thousand, tempeh 1 thousand, hot tea 3 thousand. The cat rice is a bit expensive, but the portion is really big, 1 bowl of rice. The rice is also fresh from magic com, portioned and placed on a plate and topped with anchovy sauce. Apart from anchovy chili sauce, there is also the option of stir-fried liver. The anchovy sauce is quite delicious, spicy and tasty with anchovies that dont disappoint. The tempeh is thin, so 1 thousand is a bit expensive but thats okay. It is also called the price of angkringan at the tourist center. The hot tea is okay, standard. The place is right after the first gate of the alun-alun from the direction 0km. You can sit inside the rather spacious lesehan, outside there is also 1 long table and chairs. Also available on the 0km sidewalk bench. The atmosphere is quite serene, having fun hanging out at 0km. There is no sink, no tissue. Payment must be in cash. Overall pretty good, a bit pricey but understandable for a tourist spot. The calculation is still cheaper than the next door anyway. You can stop by if you want to act cool or have an upset stomach first.

Rasa standar, caramel latte sama gula aren kopinya berasa dan buat seharga gitu cukup enak dan banyak. Cuma rasa caramel dan gula arennya gak terlalu beda, sekilas mirip. Cinnamon rollnya secara rasa lumayan enak, dan murah cuma 18k. Cuma teksturnya gak kaya cinnamon roll yang seharusnya chewy bread gitu, justru kaya pastry croissant.
review_translated_text: Outdoor indoors available. The indoor AC is hot, so its stuffy. The outside is no problem, the view from the side of the mall is towards Gito Gati. Service must be improved, as long as serving is distracted. Continue chatting with the barista, its loud again. So I dont focus, and I dont say thank you. Yes, it should be normal, dont chat while serving orders. Standard taste, caramel latte with palm sugar coffee tastes and for that price its quite tasty and plentiful. Only the taste of caramel and palm sugar is not too different, at first glance they are similar. The cinnamon roll tastes pretty good, and is cheap, only 18k. Its just that the texture isnt like a cinnamon roll which should be chewy bread, instead its like a croissant pastry.

Minus: no free WiFi.

Ibar Malioboro adalah sebuah rumah makan berbentuk bar dan lounge, yang berlokasi di lantai 2, Ibis Yogyakarta Malioboro Hotel, Jalan Malioboro No. 52-58, Suryatmajan, Danurejan, Kota Yogyakarta. Terdapat area outdoor. Juga sering menampilkan pertunjukan live music dan DJ performance pada hari-hari tertentu. Juga mempunyai paket-paket tertentu untuk wine dan beverage lainnya. Juga menyediakan pilihan minuman non alkohol seperti Milky Yuzu yang segar, dengan harga Rp 25.000,-. Ibar Malioboro merupakan singkatan dari Ibis Bar and Relationship.
review_translated_text: Ibar Malioboro is a restaurant in the form of a bar and lounge, located on the 2nd floor, Ibis Yogyakarta Malioboro Hotel, Jalan Malioboro No. 52-58, Suryatmajan, Danurejan, Yogyakarta City. There is an outdoor area. Also often featuring live music performances and DJ performances on certain days. Also has certain packages for wine and other beverages. Also provides a choice of non-alcoholic drinks such as fresh Milky Yuzu, priced at IDR 25,000. Ibar Malioboro is an abbreviation of Ibis Bar and Relationship.

review_text: Kesini pas tanggal 30 desember 2018, pas malioboro lagi rame ramenya tapi tempat ini syepii sekali. Pas kesini cuma ada 4 orang di meja lain. Tempatnya sih bagus,  bersih dan pelayanan sangat sangat oke ramah. Pesen apple pie cukup enak. Tapi menurutku menunya kurang variatif, kaya gak ada gitu menu spesialnya apa atau dia spesialis di menu apa. Jadi ada indonesianya ada western tapi gak banyakk.
review_translated_text: Came here on December 30 2018, when Malioboro was busy but this place was very quiet. When I came here there were only 4 people at another table. The place is nice, clean and the service is very, very friendly. The apple pie order was quite delicious. But in my opinion the menu is not very varied, its like theres no such thing as a special menu or what menu he specializes in. So in Indonesia there are westerns but not many.

review_text: Eyang Tun has the best and most delicious Songgo Buwono   and it became my favorite!

Eyang Tun berhasil mengajak lidahku merasakan cita rasa yang berbeda, unik, dan otentik. Pastel, risoles adalah jajanan pasar yang dijual disetiap sudut Jogja dan bukan rahasia umum lagi, rasanya sering bikin trauma. Tapi Eyang Tun (lagi lagi) berhasil membuat lidahku takjub. Kulit pastel: renyah, gurih, terasa pake susu dan keju (padahal tidak pakai) dan ketebalan kulitnya pas. Isinya: telur bacem (khas Jogja), daging sapi, wortel, dan kaya rempah. Kalo gini, aku jadi tau kalo tekstur dan cita rasa antara  Pastel dan Jalangkote (jajanan khas Makasar) itu beda! Risoles ragout ayam juga juara!. Ketebalan kulit pas, ga terlalu tebal dan terasa gurih (ga hambar). Isi ragout ayamnya manis dan gurih. Ini jajanan yg aku ga temuin dimana-mana, yi Songgo Buwono. Wah cerdas sih, tekstur Susnya kering, ladanya terasa, gurih banget. Mayones asem yg dibuat sendiri bener-bener memperkaya rasa. Oo satu lagi. Aku makan ayam afrika panggang. Wah rasanya bener2 baru bagi lidahku. Unik, adalah kata yg tepat utk menggambarkan rasanya. Makanan ini membuktikan kalau pangan dan cita rasa itu ga terbatas ruang. Aku benar-benar merasakan, setiap elemen panganan ini punya rasanya sendiri, dan ketika disatukan saling berpadu. Pas! Eyang Tun, terima kasih ya sudah memberi kesempatan lidahku merasakan cita rasa panganan elit zaman kolonial di Jogja!
review_translated_text: Eyang Tun succeeded in inviting my tongue to taste different, unique and authentic flavors. Pastels and rissoles are market snacks sold in every corner of Jogja and its no secret that their taste often causes trauma. But Eyang Tun (again) managed to amaze my tongue. Pastel skin: crunchy, tasty, tastes like it uses milk and cheese (even though it doesnt) and the thickness of the skin is just right. It contains: bacem eggs (typical of Jogja), beef, carrots and rich spices. In this way, I know that the texture and taste between Pastel and Jalangkote (a typical Makasar snack) are different! The chicken ragout rissoles are also a winner! The thickness of the skin is just right, not too thick and tastes delicious (not bland). The chicken ragout filling is sweet and savory. This is a snack that I cant find anywhere, yi Songgo Buwono. Wow, thats clever, the texture of the milk is dry, the pepper is delicious, its really tasty. Homemade tamarind mayonnaise really enriches the taste. Oh, one more thing. I ate grilled African chicken. Wow, this taste is really new to my tongue. Unique, is the right word to describe the taste. This food proves that food and taste are not limited by space. I really feel that each element of this food has its own taste, and when put together they complement each other. Fit! Eyang Tun, thank you for giving my tongue the opportunity to taste the taste of colonial era elite food in Jogja!

review_text: Eyang Tun ini spesialis jajanan dan masakan Indonesia yag terinfluens Eropa. Barusan COD pesenan berupa pastel, risoles dan songgo buwono. Enak banget, pastelnya walau isi daging gak kering--moist banget. Ragout sapi dalem risolesnya juara. Songgo buwononya juga enak banget, dengan mayones mustard homemade yang manis asem. Aku belum nemu lagi yang jual jajan songgo buwono. Pokoknya recommended banget sih, will def order more next time.
review_translated_text: Eyang Tun is a specialist in Indonesian snacks and dishes with European influences. Just ordered COD in the form of pastels, risoles and songgo buwono. Its really delicious, even though the pastel is filled with meat, its not dry - its really moist. The beef ragout in the risoles is a winner. The songgo buwono is also really delicious, with sweet and sour homemade mustard mayonnaise. I havent found anyone selling songgo buwono snacks yet. Anyway, really recommended, will definitely order more next time.
